title: pineapple cake
directions: Dump pineapple into a 13 x 9 inch cake pan.
Pour cake mix from box on top of pineapple into pan.
Cut stick of margarine on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: red bean (pinto) casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the bottom with tortilla chips. Put a sprinkle of picante sauce on each.
Use precooked pinto beans (1 quart).
Layer hamburger (cooked and drained).
Add onions, then top with chili.
Sprinkle cheese (optional) on top. Put in oven for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: carrots vichy
directions: Slice and cook carrots with salt, water and butter until tender.
Add sugar and marjoram and toss well.
Stir in cream. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve hot.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion, salt, pepper and chili powder until meat is brown; add taco sauce, soup, and tomato sauce.
Cover bottom of 13x9 inch dish with chips; put meat mixture on top.
Top with cheese and put into 350° oven to melt cheese.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Marinate
chicken in salad dressing in a sealed plastic bag overnight.	Bake
on
a rack in a 12-inch Dutch oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: no-bake summertime cookies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients, then form into small balls.
Roll each into flaked or shredded coconut.
Refrigerate until firm, 1 to 2 hours.

title: deluxe meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except soups.
Form mixture into walnut sized balls.
Brown meatballs in skillet in small amount of oil.
Drain on paper towel and place meatballs in a single layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine soups with 1 can of water; pour over meat balls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with seasoned rice or use as hors d'oeuvres!
Even people who don't care for sage rave over these meatballs!
Great made ahead dish for parties or holidays!
Freeze and reheat for a hectic day!

title: potato latkes(pancakes)
directions: Combine and mix ingredients well.
Drop by the tablespoon onto hot, greased skillet.
Flatten to taste.
Fry on both sides until brown.
Serve with applesauce.

title: green baked beans
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until it starts bubbling in the middle.

title: sweeter muffins
directions: Beat egg with fork; stir in milk and oil.
Blend dry ingredients.
Stir in just until flour is moistened.
The batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender or 2 knives, until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed. Combine buttermilk, egg and baking soda; stir into flour mixture just until it is moistened.
Turn into greased 1-quart casserole. Mark the dough in quarters with a sharp knife, cutting at least 1/2-inch deep.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add rest of ingredients. Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion and water in large saucepan. Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, bouillon and butter.
Bring to a simmer, stirring frequently.
Blend sour cream and flour in small bowl.
Stir into soup.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: lime (orange) slime(salad)
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 2 cups of cold water or substitute any juice from drained fruit.
Let jello begin to gel.
Then add lemon pudding; mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Add drained fruit and 1 cup marshmallows, if desired. Chill until firm.

title: self-filling cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Fill cupcake pans.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, salt and egg.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon on each cupcake.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meatless lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute eggplant and garlic in margarine. Add spaghetti sauce and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Layer half of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger-corn bake
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion until onion is tender.
Stir in corn, soups, sour cream, pimento and seasonings. Stir in drained noodles.
Turn into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter, then sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients together, adding the cooking oil last. Stir until mixture has consistency of cookie dough.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan which is greased and floured.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Add layers of potatoes, onion and green string beans.
Add as many layers as desired.
Top with ground beef.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour soup over the top. Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fire rice
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Prepare rice as directed. Add all spices to ground beef along with the vinegar and rice. Blend well.
Add chopped jalapenos, if desired.

title: flat beef enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add seasonings.
Soften tortillas by dipping them in hot oil,
then drain on paper towels. Dip tortillas in heated enchilada sauce and layer on individual plates with meat mixture and cheese.
Place plates in a 350° oven to melt cheese.
Serve with shredded lettuce and tomato.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and slice.
In bowl, beat egg well, then add milk, salt and pepper to your taste.
Then dip eggplant in milk mixture.
Roll in flour.
Fry in skillet of hot cooking oil until golden brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Make soup mixture in bowl with all ingredients except chicken, tortillas and cheese.
Line casserole in layers 3 times: tortillas, chicken, soup, and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream and smooth the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Whip eggs and cornstarch, then lemon juice and sour cream.
Add the portions, then add milk slowly.
Bake in a water bath at 350° until the top cracks, but not too brown.
Let cool and take out of pan.
Yields 3 cheesecakes.

title: maxine wyckoff's peach spice cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Place in ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool in pan; when cool, remove from pan and spoon on glaze.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, but don't let stand.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange stuffing across center of dish, leaving space on both sides for chicken. Add 3 chicken pieces to each side of stuffing, overlapping if necessary.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: schnitzel(veal)
directions: Rub garlic into veal.
Pound veal until it's very thin.
Brown in skillet, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Beat eggs, salt, dry mustard and milk. Layer bread, meat and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake next morning at 350° for 45 minutes.
This recipe can easily be cut in half to serve fewer people.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 360°.
Blend cake mix, nectar, oil and sugar. Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each egg. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
While cooling, mix and add cucumbers, onion, cottage cheese and salad dressing.
Looks nice molded.

title: pumpkin cheese bread
directions: Combine sugar, softened cream cheese and margarine.
Mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well until moistened. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pans.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Cook pasta shells.
Mix remaining ingredients except for spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Place in large baking dish.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in pan; cook over medium heat until marshmallows are melted.
Add jello to mixture and stir until dissolved.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add to hot mixture and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into bowl and chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise; blend well.
Pour into a 2-quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: tutty-fruity ice cream *
directions: Mix and pour into gallon freezer.
Skimmed milk and skimmed evaporated milk still works very well.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt and cider.
Tie spices in small piece of cheesecloth.
Add spices.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes. Remove spices.
Serve hot with twist of orange peel.
Use cinnamon sticks as muddle.
Makes 10 servings.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Keeps for couple of weeks (covered) in refrigerator.
Very moist and popular with men.

title: frozen biscuits
directions: Mix shortening and flour together with your fingers or pastry cutter.
Add milk and will be a sticky dough.
Place on a lightly floured board; handle gently until firm enough to roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out biscuits and place on a cookie sheet in freezer 1 to 2 hours.
When frozen, remove from cookie sheet and place in a plastic bag.
When ready to cook, remove amount of biscuits needed and place in a pan in a cold oven.
Do not preheat oven.
Turn oven to 450° and bake.
Biscuits will be ready in 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lime salad
directions: On low heat stir pineapple (with juice) and dry jello until bubbly.
Stir in cream cheese until well blended.
Add Cool Whip, stir until blended.
Add nuts and chopped cherries.
Refrigerate until completely set.
Makes a pretty Christmas dish with green and red.

title: easy but tasty casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package and drain.
Brown meat and onion; sprinkle with salt and pepper and pour off grease.
Mix soup, 1/2 can water and spaghetti sauce.
Add meat and stir in noodles.
Put in greased baking dish and top with your favorite cheese.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together, then roll in little balls and flatten out on ungreased cookie sheet.
(Can roll balls in a cinnamon sugar mixture before placing on cookie sheet.)
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Add rest of ingredients. Boil 20 minutes, seal while hot in sterilized jars.
Makes 10 pints.

title: christmas punch
directions: Note:
Be sure to use crushed ice.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Prepare sauce:
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook onion in hot oil (until tender).
Add tomatoes and their liquid, tomato paste, sugar, herb seasoning, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 3/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: basic pastry(make in food processor)
directions: Lock bowl in position and insert steel blade.
Add flour, shortening and salt; process on high speed for about 8 seconds or until the mixture resembles corn meal.
Process at high speed and add water through the chute; continue processing at same speed just until a ball forms around the blade.

title: jam-filled cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix until smooth.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture. Blend well. Cover and chill.

title: green pepper, onion and carrot medley(serves 8)
directions: Cut green peppers into strips.
Thinly slice onions.
Cut carrots into matchstick-thin strips.
In 8-quart Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook green peppers, onions, carrots, salt, basil and black pepper, stirring, until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: oven fried fish fillets
directions: Cut fillets into serving size pieces.
Coat fish with mixture of water and mayonnaise.
Combine bread crumbs, parsley flakes and paprika in a shallow dish.
Press fish fillets into crumb mixture to coat both sides.
Place on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: cranberried sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in saltwater to cover until tender.
Drain; peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes in half; place in large baking pan. Drizzle butter over potatoes; sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: lemon delight
directions: Work the flour and oleo together like pie crust.
Work in the nuts.
Press into an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: petit fours cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter and lightly flour a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll or sheet cake type pan.
Beat the eggs and egg yolks until they are blended.
Gradually add the sugar and beat until very pale color and fluffy, about 10 minutes with an electric beater.
Sift the flour and baking powder over the egg mixture.
Add the milk and fold together lightly until the batter is well mixed.
Add the melted butter and combine thoroughly. Spread the batter in the pan and bake for 12 to 15 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Turn the cake out onto a sheet of wax paper and cool completely.
Cut into small squares, rectangles or other shapes.
Arrange them in rows on a fine mesh cake rack with plenty of space between the rows.
Set the cake rack over the cake pan you baked in or a piece of wax paper.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Use jelly roll pan or 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Can be put in a 17 x 11-inch pan also.
Cool 5 minutes and ice.
It is good to have icing ready before cake is done.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat lemonade concentrate in large bowl for 30 seconds.
Blend in ice cream gradually.
Add Cool Whip and coloring; whip until smooth.
Freeze until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie crust. Freeze again for 4 hours or until frozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, then add sugars; mix well.
Beat in eggs, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, soda and powder. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Stir in marshmallow cream and peanut butter.

title: clark bar dessert
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add yolks and vanilla.
Beat.
Add Cool Whip to custard.
Put wafers or cake into 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread mix over.
Crush candy and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
If salad becomes dry, add more Cool Whip or strawberries.

title: five flavored pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening until fluffy and light. Add eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. While cake is hot, pour on glaze or use brush.

title: deodorizer for holding tanks
directions: Pour ingredients in gallon bottle.
Fill rest of bottle with water.
Use 1 cup per 4-gallon tank after every time you flush holding tank.
Works great.

title: bread bowl dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cut top off of bread bowl and hollow out.
Save pieces of bread to dip.
Spoon mixture in bread bowl.
(Use bread, chips, etc. to dip.)

title: taco casserole
directions: Arrange ingredients in order listed in 2 buttered 12-cup casserole dishes.
Bake 25 minutes in a 425° oven until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg; mix.
Combine carrots, orange and lemon rind and juice.
Add.
Sift dry ingredients; add to butter.
Add nuts; blend well.
Pour into greased 1-quart pan. Cover with 3 layers wax paper.
Put 2 cups of hot water in steamer; set pudding pan on rack.
Cover; place over high heat. When steam escapes, reduce heat to low.
Steam about 30 minutes in pressure cooker or about 2 hours in steamer.
Serve hot with Orange Sauce.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in medium saucepan. Cook over low heat until berries are soft, about 15 minutes.

title: granny's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix together sugar, shortening and buttermilk.
Blend in 4 cups of self-rising flour, 1 cup at a time.
Cover lightly and refrigerate overnight or 3 to 4 hours before using.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter and let rise 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roro's casserole
directions: Mix Veg All, cheese whiz, onion, mayo, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Crumble crackers over top of casserole. Squeeze butter over crackers.
Bake 350 for 20 minutes until bubbly and browned on top.
You may need to put casserole dish on baking tray as it tends to bubble over while cooking.

title: quick baked pike fillets
directions: Heat oven to 500°. Season fillets with salt and pepper; dip in flour. Place in lightly greased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Drizzle with butter. Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: caramel nougat roll or pecan log
directions: Mix sugar, 1/2 cup syrup and water well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil; cook, without stirring, until it reaches firm-ball stage (252°).

title: peach stuff
directions: Sprinkle 1 cup crumbs in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Cream confectioners sugar, butter, egg and vanilla in mixer bowl for 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Spread in prepared dish. Combine peaches and sugar in bowl.
Pour over creamed mixture. Spread with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup crumbs.
Chill, covered, for 2 hours or longer.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Cut and slice cucumbers and soak in lime water mixture.
Soak 24 hours or overnight.
Take out and soak in clear water 2 hours or more.
Take out and drain very well (I use a thirsty, thick towel), then put in a mixture of sugar, vinegar and spices. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Seal.
Very easy, good and crunchy.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil. Beat well. Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon and add to the mixture. Stir in pears and pecans (optional).
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: oven round steak
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole and bake, covered, for 2 hours at 350°.
This makes a great crock-pot dish.
Serve with rice or noodles and a salad.

title: fresh cobbler
directions: Mix first
ingredients.
Place peaches in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt
butter
and
pour
over peaches.
Pour the mixed ingredients
over the peaches.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Combine ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on low overnight.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Put the dill in a quart jar.
Fill with sliced pickles.
Put the garlic on top.
Heat the vinegar, water, salt and sugar to a boil.
Pour over the pickles.
Cold pack until boiling point.
Do not let them boil.
Remove jars right away.
The are ready to eat in 2 weeks.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: onion ring loaf tony roma style
directions: Slice onions crosswise and separate into rings.
Soak rings in mixture of milk, eggs and salt to taste in a bowl for 30 minutes.
Dip each onion ring in pancake mix and fry in oil heated to 375° until golden brown.
Pack fried onions loosely, without pressing (do not pack firmly), into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn onto serving plate. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar. Separate egg yolks from whites. Beat egg whites until stiff. Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tests done.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 24 (2 x 2-inch) squares.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and rinse in cold water.
Drain well.
Toss in large bowl.
Add to the spaghetti the dressing and seasoning. Chill, then add vegetables and marinate for 48 hours.
Keeps several days.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown .
Shut off oven.
Leave cake in oven for 1 hour.

title: three "p" salad
directions: Cut up fruit and drain well.
Beat whole eggs and add sugar and lemon juice.
Cook in double boiler until it is thick.
Let cool.
Mix with fruit.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into mixture after it has cooled.
Nuts and bananas may be added.

title: breaded steak
directions: Pound the steak thin; season with salt and pepper and Calamansi juice about 20 minutes before cooking.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Dip in egg just to moisten and roll in crumbs again.
Pan fry in oil over moderate heat.
Serve hot.

title: banana crunch salad
directions: Wash, core and slice the apples.
Quickly dip them into the lemon juice; let drain.
Peel and slice bananas.
Quickly dip them into the lemon juice; let drain.
In a medium size mixing bowl, combine the mayonnaise and softened peanut butter until well mixed.
Stir the sunflower seeds into the mayonnaise mixture. Stir the apple slices into the mayonnaise mixture until all slices are well coated.
Put lettuce leaves on small plates.
Spoon the banana mixture onto the lettuce leaves; sprinkle with peanuts. Serves 6.

title: party candy caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
In a large roasting pan, combine popcorn and pretzels; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil (12 to 14 minutes).
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until candy thermometer reaches 238° or a small amount of mixture dropped into ice water form a soft ball (4 to 6 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda.

title: french silk pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 5 minutes after each addition. Pour into pie shell. Chill and top with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: see's fudge
directions: In a saucepan, heat sugar and milk together over medium to low heat; stir constantly to avoid crystallization.
Bring to a boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in a half of a package of mini marshmallows, butter, chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine egg, corn, half of cracker crumbs, milk, onion and pepper. Mix well. Place in casserole dish. Combine remaining cracker crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over top of corn mixture. Bake for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: fruit and angel dessert
directions: Break cake into bite-size pieces and arrange half of it in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half the undrained pineapple and cherries.
Spread half the topping over all and top with half of the coconut.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: texas hot cocoa cake
directions: Add butter and Crisco to water and bring to a boil.
Sift flour, sugar and cocoa in a large bowl.
Pour hot liquid over flour mixture and beat until smooth. Add eggs, milk, soda, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend flour, cocoa and sugar in top of double boiler; add eggs and milk and heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add a little vanilla (1/2 teaspoon) and butter or margarine to thickened mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from reserved egg whites and brown in oven.

title: winter chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, then the heavy cream, milk, salt and vanilla.
Fold in the bananas.
Freeze.

title: stromboli
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir in flour and salt. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 7 minutes. Let rise in a warm place 2 hours. Divide into 8 balls. Let rest. Roll dough into circles. Fill with desired fillings and fold in half. Arrange on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll thin and let stand 20 minutes. Roll up and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Spread the slices out and dry 2 hours.
Drop noodles into boiling salt water.
Cook, uncovered, for about 10 minutes.
Drain and serve with your choice of meats, etc.

title: peanut butter streusel pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and confectioners sugar until mealy consistency.
Sprinkle half of mixture in bottom of pie shell. Cook pudding with 2 cups of milk until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/4 peanut butter mixture to pudding.
Pour pudding into pie shell.
Allow to cool.
Top with Cool Whip after it has cooled.
Sprinkle with remaining peanut butter mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together the wheat flour, white flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder; set aside.
Beat until creamy the oil, sugar, vanilla, zucchini and nuts.
Add the flour mixture.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Put yogurt and strawberries in blender.
Mix.
Add ice cubes. Put on frappe speed until thick.
Add more ice to make thicker.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine cooked noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, onion, celery, green pepper, pimentos and salt. Blend soup and milk.
Heat through. Add cheese.
Heat and stir until melted. Add to noodle mixture. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexi-burgers with cheese
directions: Mix beef, taco sauce, egg, bread crumbs, oregano, chili powder, cumin, salt, pepper and liquid seasoning in a medium size bowl until combined.
Shape the meat into four 4-inch burgers. Cook the hamburgers in oil in skillet for 3 minutes on each side or until the burgers are the desired doneness.
Split the buns in half.
Place a burger on the bottom of each bun.
Top the burgers with the Cheddar cheese, tomato, green pepper and top of bun.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and save 1 cup for crumb topping. To remainder, add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 35 minutes in a greased and floured square or oblong pan. Can make cupcakes also.

title: flour tortillas(makes about 12)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add water by tablespoon to make
it soft and manageable.
Knead dough 20 times. Let rest 10 minutes.

title: ritz cracker cookies(great snack)
directions: Mix and cook to a boil in double boiler.
Spread between 2 Ritz crackers until batch is gone.
Bake for 8 minutes at 300°. Can eat immediately or freeze.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix eggs and salt together.
Gradually add flour until it forms a stiff dough.
Divide dough in half and roll each until approximately 1/2 inch thick.
Cut ring of dough into strips approximately 1 inch thick and about 6 inches long.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, cocoa, cornstarch, baking powder, soda and salt.
In medium bowl, with whisk, stir sugar and water for 1 minute.
Add egg and corn syrup; stir until blended.
Gradually stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 16 servings (140 calories, 0 fat and 0 cholesterol).

title: sarah's chicken
directions: Cook and cut up 2 or 3 chicken breasts.
Mix celery and chicken soup with sour cream and add chicken.
Mix well.
Fix cornbread stuffing mix as directed on package, using chicken broth instead of water and add butter.
Top the chicken mixture with stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until is bubbly and golden brown on top.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Combine juice from canned pineapple and lemon.
Heat and thicken with cornstarch.
Add marshmallows and pineapple; let stand overnight.
Add grapes, nuts, apple, cherries and oranges.
Can use other fruit, if you like.
Put together with whipped cream.

title: shirley's salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and almost all of the pineapple.
Add nuts.
Dissolve jello in water and let thicken and add cream cheese mixture.
Add whipping cream. Let congeal.

title: banana cake
directions: Using an electric hand mixer, in medium bowl beat until creamy the margarine, sugar and eggs, then add banana(s) and beat well. Add dry ingredients right into banana mixture; beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Ovens vary so test after 30 minutes with toothpick in middle of cake.)

title: german pound cake
directions: All ingredients must be at room temperature.

title: orange-charlotte
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Pour boiling water over it. Add sugar, orange juice and lemon juice while hot.
Mix thoroughly; set in refrigerator or freezer until it is quite stiff.
Whip cream; fold into gelatine mixture along with pieces of cake.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Set in refrigerator at least 1 hour, the longer, the better.
Serves 12.

title: rice custard
directions: Heat milk slightly.
Add to beaten eggs along with salt and sugar.
Pour into casserole.
Add rice and raisins.
Place dish in pan of water.
Dot pudding with water.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: betty's hot dish
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix with egg noodles, cheese, soup and milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cover with chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: spicy pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust for 9-inch nonstick spring-form pan.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Add peanuts.
Cook on moderate heat, stirring constantly, until all liquid has boiled out.
Sugar will start to crystallize around the sides of pan. Immediately spread on cookie sheet, breaking apart any clumps. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until well dried out.

title: empanada shell
directions: Soak achote in water; rub a bit to get a darker reddish-orange color.
Combine masa harina and cornstarch in a bowl; mix well. Add salad oil.
Mix. Add achote water and mix again.
Roll out golf ball size pieces.
Flatten ball with tortilla press (use wax paper).
This can also be done by hand.
Do not use rolling pin. Place 2 to 3 tablespoons of filling in each piece of dough.
Close and pinch edges together so filling will not spill out.
Fry in hot oil and drain on paper towels.
Yields 24 shells.

title: low-fat pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth; prepare on griddle and serve with your favorite syrup or toppings.

title: vegetable appetizer
directions: Press crescent	rolls
onto cookie sheet. Seal perforations. Bake at
for	8 minutes. Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden
Valley
Ranch dressing mix. Spread in cooled crescent rolls.
Chop vegetables and arrange on top.

title: caramel raisin pudding
directions: Make a dough of first 6 items and spread into a greased casserole (a deep one or it will boil over in oven).
Spread raisins on top of dough.
Dissolve brown sugar and oleo in 2 cups boiling water and pour over raisins and dough in casserole. Bake at 375° for
45 to 50 minutes or until cake is done.
The dough will rise to the top and raisins and sauce will be in bottom.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: marshmallow fruit dish
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Add to Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well.

title: cream-filled cupcakes
directions: Beat eggs; add sour cream and beat.
Sift together flour, soda, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Sift into cream and egg mixture; beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Chill dough overnight.
Next day, form dough into walnut size balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar while warm.
(Dough can be frozen.)

title: fried cheese grits
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
Cook the grits in the water until absorbed.
Stir in the cheese and black pepper; pour into pan.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours.
Cut grits into 4-inch bars; remove from pan.
Coat with flour.
Arrange on cookie sheet; refrigerate 30 minutes more.
Heat 2 inches of vegetable oil. Coat grits again with flour.
Fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with cheese sauce.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Make into patties.
Place in skillet and brown on each side.
Take out and drain.
Place patties back in skillet.
Add bouillon cube in 1 cup hot water; let dissolve.
Add gravy and bouillon to patties in skillet.
Let liquid in skillet get hot, then turn to simmer for 15 minutes.

title: teddy bear popcorn
directions: Prepare popcorn as package directs.

title: plain ole' cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add egg and milk.
Mix well. Heat oil in iron skillet until hot.
Pour mixture into skillet and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bacon and baked potato soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onion and celery; cook and stir until crisp-tender.
Add broth, milk, potatoes, salt and pepper; bring just to boil, stirring constantly.
Slightly crush potatoes with back of spoon.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Reserve 2 tablespoons each of the bacon and cheese and 1 tablespoon of the green onion for toppings; set aside.
Add remaining bacon, cheese and green onion to soup just before serving.
Cook until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Serve topped with reserved bacon, cheese, green onion and sour cream.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Mix tomato soup with 1/2 soup can water (or bit more) and pour into a shallow pan large enough to accomodate 3 to 4 chops.
Place chops in pan with soup. Top each chop with a pepper ring.
Fill ring with uncooked rice, baste with soup and top with onion slice.
Cover with lid or foil and bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally during baking to keep rice moist.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Scramble eggs in 2 tablespoons of oil, breaking up into small pieces.
Set aside.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine.
Add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir and add M&M's and peanuts.
Put in greased pan and let sit.

title: souper rice
directions: Prepare any cream-style soup according to directions, then fill soup can with Minute rice and add to boiling soup.
Stir, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Mix in rest of ingredients (except nuts).
When partially set, fold in nuts. Pour into jello mold or 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together and beat 5 minutes.
Coat Bundt pan with Pam. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients well. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving with assorted fruit.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order in a 12 x 9-inch glass dish. Combine mayonnaise and sugar. Spread evenly on top of salad. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 12 servings.

title: leonard davis' taffy
directions: Mix together and add gelatin after mixture reaches rolling boil.
Cook to 260°.
Cool until it can be handled.
Add flavoring and pull.
(Leonard pulled it round a rod.)
Lay it on tile cabinet top in long rolls.

title: recipe of a military spouse
directions: With above ingredients, add 2 teaspoons elbow grease.
Let set alone for 1 year.
Marinate frequently with salty tears.
Pour off excess fat.
Sprinkle ever so lightly with money.
Knead dough until payday.
Season with international spices.
Bake 20 years or until done.
Serve with pride.

title: "fried" peas and butter beans
directions: Fix peas and beans ready for cooking.
Put them in a pot with grease and salt.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently until the peas and beans are tender.
Add just enough water to cover them.
Cook until tender.
Serve warm.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash split peas thoroughly. Add water; cover kettle and bring to a boil. Add the grated carrot, potatoes, onion and seasonings. Simmer about 2 hours or until split peas are tender. Strain; reheat. Add frankfurters and simmer about 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done.
Mix next 4 ingredients. Place chicken in casserole dish; pour other ingredients over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and bake until flavors are blended and cheese is melted.

title: diet chocolate syrup
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan.
While stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Boil for 1 minute.
Makes 1/2 cup syrup.

title: congealed apricot salad
directions: Put dry gelatin in pineapple juice in saucepan (4 cup size); bring to a boil (do not boil).
Take off heat and cool.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk, mandarin oranges and nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish and chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together and put in oblong casserole dish. Sprinkle crushed cornflakes and more melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly. Refrigerate. Hollow out a bread loaf and add dip to loaf.

title: marbled fudge bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and margarine or butter, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
With wire whisk beat in 2 cups sugar and 3 eggs until well blended.
With spoon stir in flour, salt, walnuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla until well mixed.
Evenly spread batter in pan.

title: date balls
directions: Combine egg, sugar and dates and cook over medium heat until dates dissolve; cool. Add remaining ingredients. Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cook above until thick, then let cool.
Add 1 quart fruit. Pour into baked crust or graham cracker crust.
Let set 2 hours.

title: berry-mallow yam bake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, oats and cinnamon; cut in margarine. Lightly toss 1 cup crumb mixture with yams and cranberries. Arrange mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven, then sprinkle with marshmallows.
Put under broiler until light brown.
Excellent for Thanksgiving, Christmas and any time with turkey.
Serves 6.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking soda in large bowl.
Stir in currants (raisins).
Stir in milk until moistened.
Knead 10 times with floured hands.
Flour cookie sheet.
Shape dough into 8-inch rounds.
Cut a cross in the top.
Bake at 400° about 40 minutes or until golden brown and light.

title: 5-layer blueberry tart
directions: Layer 1: Heat oven to 300°. In a small pan, melt half of the butter. Blend together with 2 cups of the graham cracker crumbs. Press into 7 x 12 pan. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, jello and cornstarch in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thickened; cool.
Line crust with sliced strawberries.
Pour filling over berries.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: indonesian spareribs
directions: Have ribs chopped in pieces.

Fry in oil until brown. Remove from pan. Fry onions and garlic in same pan until light brown. Add coriander, cumin and pepper. Saute. Add brown sugar, soy sauce and salt. Return ribs to pan. Saute. Add 1 1/2 cups water. Cover and simmer until tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin layer cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix 1 c. batter with pumpkin and spices. Pour remaining batter into crust.
Top with pumpkin batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes, or until center is almost set. Let cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: "cow country" soup
directions: Cook beef until almost tender.
Strain broth.
Pick meat from ribs and add to broth, along with fresh carrots and fresh green beans.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until done, about 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Beat sugar and vanilla into softened cream cheese until smooth.
Whip heavy cream.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into cooled shell.
Top carefully with fruit filling and chill several hours.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix crackers and butter together.
Press 2/3 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk.
Blend 4 crushed Butterfinger bars and ice cream and then add to pudding until smooth.
Pour onto crumb mix and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer and cover with whipped topping, remaining cracker crumbs and remaining crushed Butterfinger bars on top and refrigerate till ready to serve.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices. Dip each slice in milk. Dip in seasoned flour or meal with salt and pepper.
Fry in 1/2-inch hot cooking oil. Brown on one side before turning. Place on paper towels to drain. Eat hot and enjoy.

title: good-for-you-chili
directions: Combine all ingredients into a 4 to 5-quart pot.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or until bulgur is tender.
Serve with fat-free sour cream, plain no-fat yogurt, sliced scallions or shredded no-fat Cheddar cheese. Serves 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges.
Add sugar.
Let set overnight.
Dissolve jello and combine.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat butter and salad oil in skillet.
Saute onion, add corn, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cool and add cheese and well beaten egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in well-greased 9 x 11-inch casserole and set in pan of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve at once.
Serves 4. This is good with pork.

title: chicken conchalata
directions: You will need 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Slowly beat in 2 well beaten eggs.
Cook until slightly thickened (about 5 minutes). Beat in mayonnaise.
Toss over potatoes, onion, hard-boiled eggs and dill pickles.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse with cold water.
Pour bottle of dressing and Salad Supreme over spaghetti and toss.
Chop or dice vegetables; add to spaghetti and toss.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Parmesan cheese may be sprinkled over the top before serving.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or shrimp.

title: popcorn treats
directions: Mix popcorn, Rice Krispies and M&M's; set aside.
Heat over medium heat the remaining ingredients until boiling, then let boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over popcorn mixture immediately and mix. Pour into a large greased jelly roll pan.

title: easy and quick chicken pot pie(serves 4)
directions: Mix chicken, carrots, peas and potatoes with undiluted cream of chicken soup.
Put in buttered round casserole dish.
Roll out crescent rolls as one big top crust.
Put on top of chicken/vegetable mixture and bake in a 375° to 400° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until crust is a golden brown.

title: toffee
directions: Cook sugar, butter, water and corn syrup until light brown and will crack in cold water.
Quickly add pecans, stirring until coated.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet and flatten.
Lay Hershey bars on top and spread them as they melt.
Chill
until chocolate is hardened.
Break into pieces.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl beat eggs, corn syrup, sugar, margarine, and vanilla until well blended.
Arrange pecans in bottom of pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over them.
Bake 50 minutes at 350 degrees or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix and heat asparagus, juice and soup.
Put crushed crackers on bottom of buttered baking dish, then pour soup mixture over crackers.
Layer sliced eggs on top of soup mixture.
Put crushed potato chips to cover eggs and top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix together all ingredients. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Hollow out center of bread and pour dip into it.
Break up hollowed out bread for dipping; add breadsticks, raw vegetables and more bread for dipping.

title: colonel jack's old southern bourbon brownies
directions: Follow directions on box for cake brownies.
Grease 9 x 13-inch glass/metal pan.
Bake per recipe on box.
Cool before turning out onto cookie sheet.
Brush 1/3 cup of bourbon over cake and poke brownies with toothpick.
Mix 1/2 cup soft butter, 3 tablespoons bourbon and powdered sugar.
Add green coloring. Spread on top of brownies (the side you brushed with bourbon) about 1/8-inch thick.
Harden in freezer.

title: wild rice curry salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix rice, vinegar, oil, salt and curry powder.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, combine everything and place in lettuce lined bowl.
Top with almonds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: o'connell's special peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolates together.
Add peanut butter, peanuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on wax paper; let cool to set.
Can store in refrigerator if desired.
Makes a lot.

title: strawberry lime angel cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine strawberries, brown sugar, lime juice and lime peel; toss gently to mix well.
Place 1 cake slice on each of 4 serving plates.
Spoon 1/2 cup fruit over each cake slice.
Top each with 1 tablespoon whipped topping.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jello pudding brownies
directions: Combine pudding mix, flour and baking powder; mix well.
Melt butter in a saucepan; remove from heat.
Add sugar and eggs. Blend in vanilla and pudding mix.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan, then cut into bars.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onion in shortening until tender.
Combine egg and milk; add to biscuit mix and stir only until dry ingredients are moist. Add onion and half of cheese.
Spread dough in greased round layer cake pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and poppy seed. Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cut in wedges.
Serve hot.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in bowl; do not mix.
Microwave 3 minutes on High.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add vanilla. Pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut into tiny pieces.
(I use toaster oven trays, 10 x 4 3/4 x 3/4-inch).

title: fudge cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, soda, flour, salt and cinnamon, if desired; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine oleo, cocoa, salad oil and water; bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Add eggs and buttermilk; mix well. Mixture will appear thin.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Fudge Frosting.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 can of soup.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with remaining can of soup.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter-chocolate kisses
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, peanut butter, margarine and egg thoroughly.
Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder. Shape into 1-inch balls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until edges are light brown.
Immediately press candy firmly into each cookie.
Cool.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Spread this over cake batter.
Pour rest of batter over this. Smooth.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add wine, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 2 rices in chicken broth 45 minutes.
Mix raisins with rice.
Mix cooked spinach and cream cheese together.
Layer rice, spinach and mushroom/onion.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: citrus marinade for grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Add 3 to 4 pounds of chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before grilling.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Make into small walnut size balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet until brown, about 20 minutes at 350°.
This amount makes about 70 to 75 balls.
They can be refrigerated unbaked as long as a week.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salt; mix until thoroughly blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Mix and turn into an ice cube tray.
Freeze until firm (3 or 4 hours).
Cut into rectangles and serve on salad greens.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion, garlic and oregano until onion is tender.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: 4th of july cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1 egg at a time.
Bake in sheet pan as instructed on cake mix.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven and poke holes at once with round handle wooden spoon, every one-inch apart. Combine pudding and sugar; stir in milk.
Beat on low speed one minute.
Pour about half of thin pudding over warm cake into holes.
Allow rest of pudding to thicken (5 minutes), then ice the top with Cool Whip and rest of icing.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix together and spread on bun half and put under broiler until browned, 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
May also be baked at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Blend soup with water; measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture and combine with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
In large skillet, brown meat balls in shortening.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Saute ground beef till brown. Drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Using 1 8 oz can of biscuits, press each onto greased muffin pan.
Spoon meat mixture onto biscuits and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400 F for 12 minutes.

title: old time sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl; cut in shortening. Add the eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Roll out very thin on floured board; cut with floured cookie cutter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: short ribs of beef
directions: Cut short ribs into serving pieces.
Rub with cut clove of garlic.
Place in kettle and slice onion over top.
Cover with water, cover kettle tightly and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Transfer short ribs to greased baking dish; add tomatoes and seasonings. Cover and cook in slow oven at 300° for about 1 hour or until short ribs are very tender.
Remove cover for last 15 minutes so that short ribs will brown slightly.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pecans.
Line pie shell with pecans.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: olive dip
directions: Put softened cream cheese in bowl.
Add olives and pecans; mix well.
Keep in icebox until ready to eat!

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, 3 1/2 cups flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup flour, baking powder and 1/2 cup buttermilk with soda mixed in it.
Drop by teaspoon on greased pan.
Sprinkle with colored sugar if desired.
Bake at 350° until brown around edges.
Don't overbake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cream and butter well.
Boil in large kettle for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour onto a large greased plate or platter.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse and cook shrimp in ice water for 20 minutes.
Mix ingredients together.
Drain shrimp.
Mince and add the rest, mixing well.
Serve with chips.

title: batter(for fish, onion rings and cauliflower)
directions: Mix all together, adding a little ice water until batter looks like pancake batter.

title: huckleberry or blueberry "deluxe" cream pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients over low heat just long enough to thicken.
Berries should be nearly whole.
Cool.
Cream together sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Whip the cream stiff and fold into cream cheese mix.
Add berry mixture and spread into 9-inch pie shell.
Chill 1 hour or so if you can wait that long.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: party carrot salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed on package.
When it is ready to congeal, combine all ingredients in mold and chill.

title: stuffed potato
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Wash potato, cover with foil; bake approximately 45 minutes or until done (the time depends on the size of the potato).
When done cut open and scoop out inside; place in mixing bowl.
Add dressing (may need to add more if not to mash potato consistency).
Fold in bacon bits, onions and shrimp; then scoop back into potato skin.
Layer cheese slices on top; bake for an additional five minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let it cool for 3 to 5 minutes before serving.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Cook 20 minutes.
Add red food coloring if desired.

title: peanut butter cakes(tandy cakes)
directions: Heat peanut butter in microwave; spread over cooled cake. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Melt Hershey bar and spread on top. Refrigerate until served.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix meat with first 3 ingredients and form meatballs.
In medium-size skillet, heat oil over moderate flame.
Add onion, meatballs and mushrooms.
Brown meatballs, cooking 5 minutes. While meatballs brown, cook 1 cup egg noodles.
When meatballs are brown and onion soft, add 2/3 cup water and bouillon cube. Increase heat to boil.
Cover and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring several times until meatballs are tender.
Remove from heat. Combine sour cream, nutmeg and cornstarch and add to meatball mixture.
Return to moderate heat, stir until boiling.
Cook until thickened, about 1 minute.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice with water according to package directions.
Fry bacon in skillet until done.
Remove bacon, drain and set aside. Brown onions, green pepper and garlic in bacon fat.
Add ground chuck.
Cook until done.
Add tomato paste and sauce, then crumbled bacon and seasonings.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add already cooked rice to meat mixture and mix well.
Place in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserving syrup.
Cut apricots into small pieces.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; then add 1 1/2 cups syrup from fruits and then cool.
Add fruits, nuts and marshmallows. Pour into slightly oiled 9 x 13-inch pans.
Chill until firm.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a bowl.
Separate egg, place yolk in a 1 cup measuring cup and white in another small deep container.
Fill measuring cup with egg yolk with milk to make 1 cup and add to flour mixture.
Mix all ingredients well to form dough.
(I usually squish together with hands to be sure it's all well mixed.)
Place a handful of dough onto floured surface.
Work a little flour into dough so it isn't so sticky and roll with rolling pin to size of pie dish and thickness you want.
This takes patience and practice.
Recipe makes 2 to 3 two crust pies.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Blend in blender until smooth all ingredients.
Use as a dip for celery, carrots, cucumber, raw cauliflower, green pepper, etc. Thin with more skim milk and use as a high protein salad dressing.
Each serving amount:
1/4 cup.
Exchanges:
1 meat (protein).
Calories:

title: heath bar cheesecake
directions: Crush wafers into fine crumbs.
Mix with butter and press into greased 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle half of Heath bars over crust.
Refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Beat in 1/2 cup cream, eggs and vanilla.
Continue beating 10 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well; refrigerate overnight.
Next day, shape into ball and roll in almonds.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream well butter, sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla; gradually add well-beaten eggs.
Sift together salt, flour, baking powder and cocoa.
Add alternately with milk, starting with and ending with flour.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in well-greased and floured pan at 325° to 350°.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Blend in blender for 3 minutes.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put in as much coconut as you want.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 1 minute.
Add sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Beat well.
Add soda, salt and spices.
Fold in flour and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Spread batter onto a greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: philly delight
directions: Melt butter and add cake mix, 1 egg and pecans; mix by hand. Pour mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and spread.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese at medium to high speed until smooth and spread on top of cake.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool about 1 hour and cut.

title: baked cauliflower and cheese
directions: Cut cauliflower into small pieces.
Make medium white sauce. Melt shortening in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and add milk slowly, stirring constantly until sauce boils and thickens.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Place cauliflower in baking pan; add white sauce and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
This makes 1 cup white sauce and recipe needs 2 cups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken, debone and dice.
Combine chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add chicken and next 5 ingredients. Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: abbey's christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs and vanilla extract, if desired, into mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick on well-floured board.
(This dough works better if you refrigerate it for 2 to 3 hours.)
If you want, add food coloring and then cut into Christmas trees, stars, wreaths or fancy shapes using well-floured cutters.
Place cookies on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
If desired, place small square of milk chocolate bar on each cookie.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and brown in skillet; salt and pepper steak.
When steak is browned on both sides, put in heavy pot or pressure cooker.
Add onion, bell pepper, tomato soup and canned tomatoes.
If using pressure cooker, cook 25 minutes.
If using heavy pot, bake 1 hour in oven at 375°.

title: chicken enchiladas with green chili and vegetables
directions: Line greased 2-quart or 11 x 7-inch baking pan with tortillas (bottom and sides).
Sprinkle with layer of carrots, then layer of spinach, then onion and chicken.
Mix sour cream, milk and soup with the chilies and pour over top, completely covering veggies. Cover with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then at 350° until soup mix is bubbling (30 or 40 minutes).

title: black bean salad with mangoes-salsa
directions: *I use canned fresh mangoes found in refrigerator section of Giant.
These are already peeled and pitted, packed in a light syrup which can be drained.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients until well blended.
Blend in the next 6 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell (unbaked) and bake for 45 to 60 minutes in a 10-inch pie shell at 350° until center is done (knife inserted comes out clean).

title: rose's party mix
directions: Mix together in a large pan, Cheerios, Chex, pretzels, Kix and nut meats.
Melt oleo; add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and onion powder.
Mix well and pour over first mixture.
Preheat oven to 300° and bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well and shape into ball size.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: yoder chicken pie
directions: Place cooked chicken in bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add rice.
Heat and mix well together the soups, broth and margarine; pour over rice.
Add sliced eggs on top. Cover with foil and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chestnut baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking pan.
Bake at 350° until bacon is crisp on top.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef in skillet.
Pour off excess grease.
Mix all other ingredients together with the ground beef in large casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cranberry yogurt coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, blend the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, yogurt and oil.
Beat with an electric beater on high for 3 minutes.
Scrape the bowl often. Spread 2/3 of the batter in the prepared pan.
Spoon the cranberry sauce evenly over the batter.
Spoon the remaining batter evenly over the cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Makes 20 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions, Worcestershire and m.s.g.
in a large bowl.
Cut chipped beef into small pieces.
Make a ball with the mixture and top with the pieces of chipped beef. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: If peppers are large, cut in half.
Cut off slice on top and remove seeds.
Fill 1 pepper with rice stuffing (all the other ingredients combined) for each person.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in oiled casserole dish.
Serve with tomato soup.
Serves 6.

title: date cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: kraut
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour this mixture over other ingredients.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute onion and ground beef.
Pour off fat.
Drain juice from tomatoes in the pot with the meat and onion.
Chop whole tomatoes and add.
Put in water, cubes, beans, celery, seasonings and carrots.
Add cabbage and bring to boil, then cook on low for an hour or until cabbage is tender.

title: pineapple creme de menthe
directions: Shake in a cocktail shaker with crushed ice.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil add one cup of flour immediately. Stir until it forms a ball. Let cool for five minutes. Beat into mixture one at a time. Mix until smooth. Spread in a a greased 9 x 13 inch pan bake at 400 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes or until golden. Cool completely.

title: lorraine's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and save the juice.
Line the bottom of a sprayed 9 x 15-inch baking pan with cut-up chicken.
Spread sliced onion over chicken.
Mix soups and milk until blended and bring to a simmer, then pour over chicken.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all, refrigerate and enjoy.

title: martha's breakfast casserole(great for overnight company)
directions: Brown sausage, drain and cool.
Beat eggs and milk together. Add salt and mustard and beat again.
Add bread and stir until soft.
Stir in cheese, mushrooms and sausage.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.
Increase baking time if recipe is doubled.

title: simply savory potatoes
directions: Place potatoes into slow cooker. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over potatoes and stir. Cover and cook on high for 4 hours.

title: baked chicken pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Lay 4 to 6 pieces of chicken breast on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle 1 box of chicken Shake 'n Bake on top. Cover tightly with tin foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: suet pudding
directions: Steam for 2 hours.

title: walnut chicken
directions: Skin, halve and bone chicken breasts.
Cut chicken into 1 inch pieces.
In a small bowl stir soy sauce into cornstarch; stir in chicken broth, ginger root, sugar, salt and red pepper.
Set aside. Preheat a wok over high heat; add cooking oil.
Stir-fry green peppers and green onions in hot oil for 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from wok.
Add walnuts to wok; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until just golden.
Remove from wok.
Add half of the chicken to the hot wok; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove from wok. Stir-fry remaining chicken 2 minutes.
Return all chicken to wok. Stir soy mixture into chicken.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and walnuts; cover and cook 1 minute more.
Serve chicken and vegetables at once with hot cooked rice. Garnish with whole red peppers and fresh cilantro, if desired.

title: turkey hash
directions: In medium nonstick skillet, cook the turkey and onions over medium heat about 5 minutes or until the turkey is no longer pink and the onions are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add the potatoes. Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Stir in the cheese, onion powder, garlic powder, sage, thyme and pepper.

title: orange scallops
directions: Combine zest, juice, oil and scallops in a plastic bag; refrigerate 1 hour.
Broil scallops 4 inches from heat, 6 minutes until dull in color.
Add parsley.
(136 calories, 19 protein, 4 grams fat.)

title: coconut pie
directions: Bowl must be bake type.
Place fruit in flat bowl.
Add sugar and butter and let warm in oven to melt butter.
Add cake mix over top of mixture and let cook slowly in the oven until done.

title: st. anne's brunch casserole
directions: Refrigerate overnight for baking next morning.
Use a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Butter bottom of pan.
In bowl, mix eggs with milk, add salt, mustard and pepper.
Beat till well blended.
Set aside. Place bread cubes in bottom of pan, (enough to cover bottom). Layer cheese (and optional ingredients).
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Top with croutons and dot with butter.
Refrigerate covered over night.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes. Serves 12.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Lard the venison with salt pork.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except sour cream, with equal parts of red wine and water.
Bring to a boil and allow to simmer for 30 minutes.
Add the venison and cover.
Simmer for 2 hours and then remove the meat.
Strain the sauce and place venison in a roasting pan.
Pour the liquid over the roast and add the sour cream.
Cook slowly until well done.

title: dad's spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer 3 or 4 hours.
Half hour before done, add 8 ounces chopped mushrooms and 2 cups of minced clams, drained.

title: nite owl sweet rolls
directions: Spread nuts in bottom of greased tube pan (or 9 x 13-inch baking dish).
Arrange frozen rolls over nuts.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, then dry pudding mix.
Place margarine pieces over top.
Cover and thaw overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until rolls are baked.
Turn immediately out into a serving dish.

title: peanutty chocolate treats
directions: In a bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs and butter. Mix well. Stir in sugar and peanut butter. Press mixture into a greased 8-inch square pan. In the microwave or double boiler, melt chocolate chips; stir until smooth and spread over peanut butter layer. Chill for 30 minutes or so before cutting into squares. Chill 30 minutes more until firm.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Add pineapple chunks and juice to bread cubes.
Toss.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart round casserole.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: hawaiian chicken and rice
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl; stir well, set aside. Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray and add butter. Place over medium-high heat until butter melts. Add chicken and cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned. Remove chicken from pan and set aside. Add rice and garlic to pan, and saute for 3 minutes. Return chicken, meaty side down, to pan. Add chicken broth mixture, bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 25 minutes, or until most of the liquid is absorbed. Stir in green onions and remaining ingredients; cover and cook an additional 5 minutes or until the vegetables are tender. Can be served with sweet and sour sauce.

title: "delicious" cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
As cake bakes, simmer together pineapple and sugar.
As you remove the cake from the oven, punch holes in it and cover with pineapple. Chill.
Mix by box directions the pudding with coconut and spread over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.

title: strawberry sorbet
directions: Combine boiling water and sugar in a large bowl, stirring until sugar dissolves; let cool.
Stir in strawberries and next 2 ingredients.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze until almost firm.
Spoon mixture into a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Return mixture to pan and freeze until firm.
To serve, let stand at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields 4 cups.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and butter.
Add egg and milk. Mix all together.
Roll out and cut into pieces; put into broth. Cook until all float to top of pan.

title: grandma's potato pone
directions: Mix eggs and sweet potato.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Bake in buttered dish for 1 hour in a moderately hot oven.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Add lemon juice mixed with egg yolks, flour and milk to sugar and melted butter.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheddar potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes until browned.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Saute onion and chicken pieces in butter.
Add spaghetti sauce and celery and simmer until celery is tender-crisp.
Add oregano and mix thoroughly.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: parmesan flan
directions: Melt 1 cup of sugar in a small pan.
When it gets caramelized, cover the inside of mold.
Mix all of the ingredients together with a mixer until everything looks uniform, then pour the mix into the mold and bake in the oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let flan cool in oven before refrigerating.
Serve chilled.

title: cajun corn bread
directions: Saute ground beef with onion and garlic; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour half mixture into large skillet.
Add ground beef mixture, then cheese.
Pour remaining batter over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 325° (don't preheat oven) for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place shredded cabbage in large buttered casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients, pouring soup over the top of all.
Bake for 1 hour or until cabbage is tender in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix first 6 ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar. Bake uncovered in a preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; pound into meat.
Brown meat on both sides.
Top with cut up onion and tomatoes.
Cover; cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Add green pepper; cook 15 more minutes.
Thicken juice if desired. Season to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot cranberry drink
directions: Heat water, red hots, sugar and cloves until red hots melt. Add juices.
Serve hot.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over top).
Boil and stir 5 minutes more; take off heat. Stir in until completely melted the chocolate chips or peanut butter chips.
Stir in vanilla and chopped nuts.
Spread in buttered 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into 30 pieces.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Cook vegetables in broth until done.
Add beef, macaroni and tomato sauce.
Serve warm.

title: easy chick n' dump
directions: Bring quart of water to boiling point.
Add chicken base (to taste).
Begin dropping flour tortillas until thickens.
Cook 20 minutes and serve with green salad.

title: chicken continental
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Brown in oil slowly.

title: beef quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brush the inside of the pie shell with a small amount of beaten eggs.
Prick bottom with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef and onions together until beef is lightly browned and onions are golden.
Drain and put into pastry shell.
Beat eggs and soup until well blended.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Cut pepper in thin strips; put strips and peas in large nonstick skillet.
Stir in rice mix and 2 cups water; bring to a boil.
Remove skin from drumsticks and place them in one layer on rice; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, covered.
Turn drumsticks; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink near the bone.
The liquid will be almost absorbed. Sprinkle with scallions.

title: shrimp or crabmeat quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Thaw pie crust as package directs. Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake on cookie sheet about 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Distribute shrimp or crabmeat over bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese and onions over shrimp.
Beat eggs, milk, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour over shrimp or crabmeat mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake an additional 15 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: trader vic's pineapple chicken
directions: Combine chicken 1/2 cup chicken stock, 1/2 cup cornstarch, flour, salt, and eggs; beat well.
Pour approximately 1-inch oil into wok.
Heat until almost smoking.
Dip pineapple and chicken into batter; cooking a few in heated oil at a time.
Drain pineapple and chicken pieces.
Pour off all but a thin coat of oil from wok.
Put garlic, pepper, and carrot into wok, and cook for 2 - 4 minutes.
Pour in vinegar, sugar, and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Quickly stir in cornstarch and chicken stock mixture.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over chicken and pineapple; serve.

title: stir-n-roll pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Measure flour, baking powder, salt, milk and 1/4 cup salad oil into bowl.
Stir vigorously until mixture leaves side of bowl.
Gather dough together and press into ball. Knead dough in bowl 10 times to make smooth.
Divide in half.
On lightly floured cloth-covered board, roll each 1/2 into 13-inch circle.
Place on pizza pan or baking sheet.
Turn up edge 1/2-inch and pinch.
Brush crust with 2 tablespoons oil.
Add your own toppings and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine water, milk and pudding mix; beat on low speed for 2 minutes. Chill for 5 minutes. Fold in the whipped topping. In individual dessert dishes, layer wafers, pudding, bananas and more pudding. Top each with a wafer. Chill until serving. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: mex chip dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In crockpot combine chili, chilies, taco sauce, and cubed cheese.
Add hamburger and mix. Heat until melted.
Stir often.
Dip chips.

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Set aside. Cook noodles according to package.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Combine noodles with tuna, celery and green onions.
Blend in sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, thyme and salt.
Spoon half the mixture into buttered two quart casserole.
Top with half the zucchini.
Repeat layers. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with chopped tomatoes.

title: china moon chili-orange oil
directions: Wash oranges with liquid detergent and abrasive sponge.
Sounds korny, but this will get rid of waxes and dyes.
Peel away a thin layer of orange zest and finely mince.
Combine minced zest with remaining ingredients in heavy nonaluminum 2 to 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to 225° to 250° on deep fry thermometer.
Stirring occasionally, let bubble for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Scrape the oil and seasonings (this is the goop) into glass or plastic container and store at room temperature.

title: indonesian chicken in lime(serves 4)
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Put to one side and saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add honey, turmeric, pepper, cumin, coriander and soy sauce.
Simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Sprinkle with lime juice just before serving.
Garnish with lime quarters.

title: turkey soup
directions: Simmer turkey bones and pieces in water with carrots, celery, salt and parsley for 2 hours.
Drain, saving broth in refrigerator until fat can be removed.
Clean turkey meat from bones.
