In kettle, put broth, turkey, diced celery, diced cooked carrots, diced onions and soup starter.
Simmer until onions and celery are done.
Add rice or noodles.
Amount will vary depending on amount of broth.
Simmer until done.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, breaking up tomatoes.
Simmer for 25 minutes and serve over pasta.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Mix well and shape into walnut size balls. Drop onto cookie sheet (ungreased) about 1 inch apart. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix hot water with jello.
Then mix all other ingredients. Chill until set.

title: italian pasta shell casserole
directions: Cook shells according to package directions. Rinse and drain. Brown ground beef in skillet. Add salt & pepper. Stir in Ragu sauce and simmer 20 minutes. Using a deep Lasagna pan or a very large casserole dish, line the bottom with half of the cooked shells. Cover the shells with half the meat sauce. Spread 1/2 pint of sour cream lightly over the sauce. Sprinkle with half of both cheeses. Repeat for the second layer in the same order. Cover the pan and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes more. Casserole is ready to serve when the cheese is melted and lightly browned. Serves 8-10.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, mix sour cream and egg.
Add to flour mix.
Add butter last.
Beat with wire whisk. Makes about 8 pancakes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Mix beef and onions in skillet.
Cook until slightly brown; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in ketchup and tomato sauce. Heat thoroughly.
Put in casserole dish.
Cut cheese into thin strips and spread over meat.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: custard
directions: Scald milk and sugar together.
Beat eggs and mix with milk. Add vanilla.
Put custard in ovenproof bowl in pan of hot water. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with nutmeg.

title: mexican salad
directions: Cook beef.
In a large bowl, combine beef, chili powder, tomatoes, onion, lettuce, beans and cheese.
Just before serving, add dressing and crushed chips.
Makes a large amount.

title: beef and tater casserole
directions: Place ground beef in casserole dish.
Slice onion over beef, then spread frozen French fries over onion.
Pour soup over French fries.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: tapioca fruit salad
directions: Drain juice and add enough water to make 3 cups.
Cook pudding in juice and water; cool.
Add oranges, pineapple, 2 or 3 bananas and 2 cups miniature marshmallows.
Suitable for salad or dessert.

title: mexican rice
directions: Fry rice in oil for about 5 minutes.
Add onion and saute until onion is tender.
Add tomato puree and 2 cups water.
Let simmer for about 20 minutes. Add peas and remaining water.
Cook until rice is tender.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: potluck potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Peel and cube.
Pour low calorie French dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onion, hard-boiled eggs (sliced) and 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine low calorie mayonnaise and prepared mustard.
Carefully mix with potato mixture.
Add celery seed, if desired.
Chill 4 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: sour cream pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt on top of double boiler; add scalded milk and stir well.
Cook over direct heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks well, stir in a little hot mixture and pour back into double boiler.
Cook over boiling water 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until light; gradually beat in 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Fold coconut into cooled filling; fold 1/3 meringue into cooled pie filling also.
Pour filling into cooled pie shell and spread remaining meringue over filling so as to touch the edges of the crust all around.
Place in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.
If desired, can put a stiff coating of whipped cream and shredded coconut on top.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into ball and refrigerate until ready to serve.
May be rolled in chopped dried beef for a nice coating before chilled.

title: vanilla ginger cookies
directions: Beat eggs, add lard and syrup and mix well.
Then add soda, ginger, vanilla and enough flour to make stiff batter.
Bake at 375°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring 2 quarts of water and cooking oil to a boil.
Add macaroni and stir to separate.
Return to boil.
Boil, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 6 minutes, then drain.
In a large bowl, combine butter, egg, salt, pepper and macaroni into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix well.
Press into pizza pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly, slice, and weigh.
In 5 gallon poly food grade bucket put one bag of Mrs. Wages lime with 2 gallons of water add cucumber slices and soak for 24 hours.
Wash off thru two waters handling carefully so not to break.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding.
Fold in cool whip, oranges and 3/4 of the cookies.
Pour into a bowl and top with the rest of the cookies.

title: broccoli-corn-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat broccoli in vented, covered dish; add water.
Cook 4 minutes in microwave.
Drain; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, butter and flour in container of a blender, process until smooth.
Set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light.
Add mashed bananas and eggs.
Stir together the flour, soda and salt, then add to banana mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in the buttermilk, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
(Makes 1 large loaf or 2 medium.)
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Place water in bowl.
Add sugar and yeast.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Blend in dry ingredients 1 minute.
Add butter, honey and egg.
Add yeast mixture while mixing on low speed.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Knead dough.
Roll into pie type flat dough shape; cut into 3 x 2-inch blocks.
Fry in deep fat at 375°.
Punch dough once to below level of oil.
Makes 25 servings.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Mix whipping cream, sour cream and Parmesan cheese together. Add garlic salt, pepper and parsley.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Add butter to noodles.
Pour cream sauce over noodles and serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: radishes and peapods
directions: Cut radishes into quarters.
Break ends off of peapods.
Heat oil in skillet or wok.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper and stir-fry.
Serve with steak and mushroom sauce.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture. Stir in chips.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Over low heat, mix pineapple juice, sugar, vinegar, flour and egg.
Stir until dissolved then refrigerate.
Cut up apples, mix with pineapple, Cool Whip and mixture.
Add peanuts when ready to serve.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into rectangles about 2 x 1 1/2-inch.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter to cream; gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in soda and flavorings.
Add sour cream and mix.
Beat in eggs, two at a time.
Beat in flour a cup at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour in buttered and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Pour into pie shells. Sprinkle 1/2 can coconut on each pie.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 275°.

title: rice-egg drop soup
directions: Combine water, salt, carrot, ginger, rice and green onion and bring to boiling; stir well.
Lower heat.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally 45 minutes.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Do not boil.
Remove carrot from saucepan and cut into thin slices.
Return to saucepan. Remove and discard ginger.

title: spinach balls #1
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: mexican peas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare peas according to cooking instructions, drain.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine and add next 3 ingredients, set aside.
Combine peas and remaining salsa and spoon into an ungreased baking dish.
Pour onion mixture over peas and bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves as a dip.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels finely.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Stir until pretzels are covered. Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Beat until completely mixed.
Spread over pretzel mixture, making sure edges are sealed.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Cook onion and butter or margarine in large pot until tender. Add water, potatoes, carrots, cooked chicken pieces, chicken bouillon cube and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add milk.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Pour melted butter into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add squash and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: chicken with walnuts
directions: Skin, halve lengthwise and debone chicken breast into 1-inch pieces; set aside.
In a small bowl, stir soy sauce into cornstarch.
Stir in dry sherry, ginger root, sugar, salt and pepper; set aside.

title: perfect sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces and cut potatoes and onions. Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into greased dish and cover with foil for about 20 to 30 minutes, or until potatoes are done.
Add shredded chilled or sliced cheese and melt.

title: old fashion walnut bread
directions: Resift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, milk, shortening and vanilla to dry mixture.
Stir just until all flour is moistened.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan or divide batter between 2 greased No. 2 1/2 cans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 20 minutes; for rectangular loaf, 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, being sure they are all bite size pieces.
Refrigerate, if desired.
Add last 3 ingredients immediately before serving.
Mix well.

title: low's salad
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: garlic broiled shrimp
directions: Shrimp may be broiled shelled or in shell, deveined.
In pan, melt butter or margarine. Stir in rest.
Place shrimp in pan, turning to coat.
Broil 3 minutes.
Turn and broil 3 minutes longer until shrimp turns pink. Serve.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy bottomed saucepan. Add carrots and onions; saute until tender. Add flour. Blend in smoothly to create a roux.
Heat milk and beer together in another saucepan. Stir heated milk mixture into onion/carrot/roux mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until liquid comes to a boil and mixture is thickened. Add shredded cheese and seasonings, stirring until melted.

title: mysterious orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.

In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, sugar, eggs, tomato soup, 1/4 cup water, flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger, about 3 minutes, until well blended, stopping mixer to scrape down sides of bowl occasionally.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until wooden pick inserted in center of layers come out clean.
Cool layers in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to rack to cool completely.

title: citrus dressing
directions: Combine orange juice, olive oil, lemon juice, honey, mustard, salt and pepper in a medium-size jar with tight-fitting lid. Shake until well blended.
Serve over favorite mixed greens.

title: tzrtziki(greek dip)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour or so. Serve with veggies, bread sticks, pretzels or ethic bread. Can substitute 1/2 cup sour cream for yogurt.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and butter.

title: fish cakes
directions: Flake fish; remove any bones. In a mixing bowl, add fish to mashed potatoes and raw egg.
When mixed well, add lemon juice, vinegar, parsley, hard boiled egg, salt and pepper.
The mixture will be rather sticky.
Shape into small rounds with floured fingers and roll into breadcrumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Fry in hot oil in frying pan over medium heat or deep fry.
Should be golden brown and crispy on the outside.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Let first 3 ingredients stand overnight.
Drain zucchini in colander and rinse.

title: amish pudding
directions: Heat milk.
Beat egg yolks with sugar and add to milk.
Add coconut and crackers.
Cook on stove until thick.
Beat egg whites. Add vanilla and fold in.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: dried beef log
directions: Mix
cream
cheese, dried beef, onion, green peppers and horseradish,
then	blend
in sour cream carefully.
Shape into log and roll in reserved dried beef.
Serve with party rye.

title: aunt hattie's scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot top with margarine.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out or press crescent rolls in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch.
Spread on cooled crescent rolls.
Top with chopped vegetables and cheese; sliced olives could be added.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Place drained broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place cooked chicken over it.
Pour soup mixture over chicken. Stir bread crumbs into melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Let margarine and cheese stand at room temperature.
Add other ingredients and roll into small balls; flatten.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: polish mistake
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage together; drain.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Spread on bread to make a sandwich.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Serve warm.

title: cheese scrambled eggs
directions: Place butter in a shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High until melted.
Add eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat with a fork to scramble.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes on High or until eggs are almost set, but very soft, stirring once.
Top with cheese.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High or until cheese is softened.
Serves 4.

title: smothered rabbit
directions: Cut rabbit
into
serving pieces; roll in flour.
Brown meat in	cooking
oil.
Start
off with hot grease, then turn heat to simmer.
Add
water and flour; cook on low heat until done. Cooking time should be about 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all together and pour over finely chopped cabbage.
Let set before serving.

title: fat free garlic dip
directions: In electric blender or food processor, blend cottage cheese, lemon juice, milk, paprika and garlic until smooth.
Stir in chives.
Chill 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve.
Contains 14 calories per 1 tablespoon serving; 0 grams total fat.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Fill cones 2/3 full with batter.
Stand on cookie sheet and bake by directions on box.
Let cool, then frost and sprinkle with sprinkles.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream the oleo and sugars.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the flour, soda and oats.
Add the chopped peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Roll in small balls and pat thin on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: homemade donuts
directions: Heat Crisco oil in deep pan.
Cut centers out of biscuits with a syrup lid.
Place donut cut biscuits in hot oil.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Dip in confectioners sugar until covered.

title: golden frosting
directions: Blend butter, 1/3 of powdered sugar, cream, salt and vanilla. Add egg and remaining sugar.
Beat until creamy and smooth.

title: old fashioned swiss steak
directions: In a large plastic bag combine 1/2 Cup flour, 1 tsp. salt, 1/2 tsp. pepper and garlic salt.
Add beef and toss to coat.
Remove meat from bag and pound with mallet. heat oil in Dutch oven and brown steak.
Add garlic, green pepper, celery and onion.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, broth, soy sauce and salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 325 for 2 hours.
Remove from oven.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Whip together Dream Whip and 1/2 cup milk. Whip together 2 cups milk and 1 large package instant vanilla pudding. Fold together Dream Whip and pudding. Add pineapple (drained) and pecans. Alternate layers of filling and vanilla wafers, beginning with wafers and ending with filling. Chill to serve.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2 1/2-quart baking dish in a 350° oven or microwave.
Combine dry ingredients and milk in bowl; mix well. Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Top with peaches.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat egg until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until lemon colored; stir in zucchini.
Mix together and add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then finish cooling on rack.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Mix together molasses, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Sift together sugars, flour, salt and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add vanilla, then add to sifted mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar with mixer and add all other ingredients in order.
Great for cookie press or refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix and add cut up chicken wings.
Blend until all chicken is covered.
Soak at least 4 hours, mixing occasionally.
Deep fry and keep warm in oven at least 250°.

title: sloppy chicken
directions: You will also need an electric skillet.
Do not turn on skillet until all ingredients have been added.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add milk, egg, onion and pepper.
Fry in hot oil by tablespoonfuls.

title: angel food cake
directions: Measure sifted flour and add 1/2 cup sugar and sift 4 times. Combine egg whites, cream of tartar and flavorings in large bowl. Beat at high speed of electric mixer or rotary beater until soft peaks form.
Add rest of sugar in 4 additions, beating until blended.
Sift in flour mixture in 4 additions folding in with large spoon.
Turn bowl often.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool upside-down in pan on cake rack.
Loosen from sides and remove.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Mash cheese; mix with pineapple.
Dissolve jello in hot water and Coke.
Mix cheese and pineapple with jello, along with the nuts.
Chill in the refrigerator.

title: four minute frosting
directions: Put in top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water. Beat 4 minutes at high speed with hand mixer.
Remove from heat. Use to frost a 2 or 3 layer cake.

title: sherbrany
directions: You will need a bowl, pot, big mixing spoon and plate.

title: brownies
directions: In a small saucepan, combine chocolate and margarine; melt over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let cool. Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl. In small bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt; add to sugar mixture and mix well. Add chocolate mixture and combine well. Pour into a foil (shiny side down)-lined 8 x 8 pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Dust with powdered sugar or ice with frosting.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut round steak into squares (same size as beef tips).
Cut green peppers into eighths.
Cook meat in skillet on medium heat (add a tablespoon of oil).
Add soy sauce, green bell peppers and desired seasonings.
After 5 minutes, mix 1 cup of flour to 2 cups of water and mix with fork (it should be a little watery, not thick).
Add to meat and cook for 30 minutes.

title: animal pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Add flour sifted with salt, baking powder and sugar; stir until well mixed.
Bake on griddle in animal shapes.
A big spoonfuls for the body and small spoonfuls for head, legs, ears, etc.
Turtles and rabbits are favorites.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms.
Turn onto surface dusted with flour.
Roll in flour to coat.
Shape into ball and knead 3 to 4 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick and cut with 2-inch cutter, dipped in flour.
Place biscuits with edges touching on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 18 to 22 biscuits.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Italian seasoning, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder in a shallow bowl.
Dip each chicken breast in beaten egg, then roll in bread crumb mixture to evenly coat.

title: the butte montana pasty (pass-tee)
directions: Measure flour and salt.
Cut in lard until dough resembles small peas.
Add water and divide into 6 equal parts.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and
cocoa	together and set aside to cool. Beat sugar and eggs together.
Mix ingredients when cool.
Add sifted flour and
salt
to the mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 350° in well-greased oblong pan for 35 to 45 minutes.
When done, push marshmallows into top of the cake.

title: sandra's southern fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, then slice potatoes in round 1/2 inch thick slices in a medium size bowl, with water.
In a cold frying pan start layering 1/2 c. of sugar, a little nutmeg and some potatoes; continue layering until all potatoes are used up.
Sprinkle sugar and nutmeg on top; cover and cook on top of stove for about 20 minutes on medium heat.
Watch closely; if the potatoes do not accumulate water, add 2 tsp. of water.
Recover and continue to cook the remaining time.
After cooing for about 20 minutes, remove lid and let the potatoes get some air.
When potatoes take on a sweet orange appearance and is tender to the touch lower the heat. You will need to remove lid several times to get the right color and texture.
When potatoes are almost done add butter, orange peel, and lemon extract; let cook for 2 minutes or until seasoning have blended nicely.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chocolate banana pie
directions: Melt chocolate, butter and 2 tablespoons milk in microwave until chocolate is melted and bubbly.
Pour in bottom of pie crust and place in freezer for 15 minutes, until chocolate is firm. Slice 2 bananas and layer slices on top of chocolate.
Mix filling mix and beat for 1 minute in a large bowl with a wire whisk.
Let set for 5 minutes and spoon over chocolate and bananas.
Place sliced bananas on top and chill for 2 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: layered taco dip
directions: For the first layer, spread bean dip on large, flat serving plate.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to pkg. directions. Pour half of the batter in a greased 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes, or until almost done.

While the cake is baking, put the sweetened condensed milk in a microwavable bowl. Unwrap the caramels and put in the bowl with the milk. Microwave for 2 minutes, stir frequently. Continue to microwave until melted, stirring frequently.
Pour the caramel mixture over the baked cake. Spread the remaining cake mixture over the caramel mixture. Bake for 10-15 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and potatoes dinner
directions: In a large baking dish, mix all the ingredients.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 2 hours.
Turn chicken and potatoes once.
Serve with green salad!

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill before serving.
May add red food coloring, if desired.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Combine cake mix and jello.
Add eggs, oil and wine.
Beat low speed until moist and 3 minutes on medium speed.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Put pecans on bottom and pour in batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.
When cake is done, pour 2/3 cup glaze on cake still in pan, while hot.
Cool 30 minutes.
Then turn cake out to cool.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or shallow ovenproof dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with tortilla chips, crackers, or assorted cocktail bread slices.

title: vegetarian layered mexican casserole with black beans
directions: Mash beans with water.
Cook onion with next 3 ingredients. Layer in baking dish, tortillas, vegetables, beans, salsa and cheese (twice).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: two tone fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, white sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly over heat, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Marshmallow Cream and vanilla; mix until smooth. To 2 cups mixture, add butterscotch and 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Heat remaining mixture and add chocolate pieces and 1/2 cup nuts.
Mix well and pour over other mixture and chill.

title: chili sauce for canning
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes and onions.
Combine with all the other ingredients.
Simmer over low heat and stir often to prevent sticking.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets, chill overnight, and shred.
Combine shredded potatoes and other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Can be divided and frozen for later use. Divide this before it is cooked. If you divide, cook half only 30 minutes.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Combine Bisquick and milk; stir until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Shape dough into ball on a floured surface.
Knead lightly 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into eight 2 1/2-inch rounds using a floured biscuit cutter.
Mix cherry pie filling with cinnamon and water. Pour into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Top with dough rounds. Bake in a 400° oven until dough topping is golden brown (about 25 to 30 minutes).

title: homemade stickers
directions: Mix together.
"Paint" on the back of your picture.
Let dry. Add a second coat.
Let dry, lick it and stick it.
Use own drawings, gift wrap, copies of photos, etc. for stickers.

title: chipped beef gravy
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Sprinkle flour over beef and mix well. Add milk and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Mixture thickens as it heats.
Let stand a few minutes before serving. May be served over bread (toasted) or fried potatoes.

title: raspberry cheese cake
directions: Chill milk.
Add boiling water to jello and stir well; cool. Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled jello. Blend well.
Chill until mixture begins to set.
Whip evaporated milk, then add to jello and cream cheese mixture.

title: easy cream of peanut soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in milk and simmer for a few minutes.
Smooth peanut butter may be substituted for a smoother soup.
Good as an appetizer.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° about 30 minutes until mixture doesn't adhere to knife.
Serve warm or cold.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Saute in frypan the onion, pepper and celery.
Cook acini de pepe (or any other small pasta) until tender and drain.
Combine sauteed mixture and acini de pepe with mayonnaise (as you would a salad) in a casserole dish.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, salt and pepper, plus catsup.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Remove from oven and pour off excess grease. Pour over meat, Spanish rice and cheese.
Return to oven and heat until cheese melts.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and celery.
Saute in drippings until almost clear; set pot off.
Add soups and tomato sauce, using 1/2 can of water in each to rinse cans, adding to pot.
Stir until completely mixed while heating on medium fire.
When soups start to boil, add crawfish, seasonings and the balance of recipe. Bring to boil again.
Lower heat to simmer for 8 to 10 minutes. Be sure to stir very often to prevent sticking or burning.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg; stir in milk and dry ingredients.
Fold in berries.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Blend salad oil and sugar.
Whip in eggs and stir pumpkin into creamed mixture.
Measure flour, salt, baking powder, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda.
Sift all together.
Then stir into pumpkin creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° until done for 40 to 45 minutes in two greased loaf pans.
Let cool before removing from pans.
Bread may be toasted or plain or spread with oleo. May be frozen.
Stays moist.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and dice or shred chicken breasts and set aside.
Cut Velveeta cheese into 1/4 inch cubes and set aside.
Blend cream soups and Rotel tomatoes in a 12 inch skillet.
Bring to a simmer. Dip one tortilla into soup mixture (cover both sides).
Lay tortilla in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Put 1 - 2 Tbsp. of chicken and 3 cubes of Velveeta cheese on tortilla and roll up.
Place rolled tortilla at end of pan.
Repeat process until chicken and Velveeta cheese are used up.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 350° for 20 - 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: swiss cheese onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Mix mushroom soup, onions and Swiss cheese.
Top with chunky hard bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, pork, salt, pepper, rice, onion and the 8 ounce can of tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly and set aside.
Separate cabbage leaves.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes or until pliable.
Spoon portions of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Roll, folding ends over. Place seam side down in Dutch oven.
Mix the two 15 ounce cans of tomato sauce with brown sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over rolls. Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting often.
Remove rolls to serving dish and thicken sauce with a mixture of cornstarch and water.
Pour over rolls and serve over hot rice.
Freezes well.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Combine meat, egg, salt and onion.
Blend well; shape into tiny balls.
Makes about 50 to 60 meat balls or use already made ones from freezer.

title: pecan waffles
directions: Combine dry ingredients and add pecan meal.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Combine with milk and melted shortening and add to dry ingredients, mixing just until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Yields 6 to 8 waffles.

title: nibblin' fish(crunchy munchies for kids)
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, combine oat cereal, pretzel sticks, fish shaped crackers and nuts.
Stir together oil and Worcestershire sauce; drizzle over cereal mixture, tossing to coat evenly.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Store mixture in tightly covered container. Makes 6 cups.

title: good-bye turkey
directions: Combine soup with broth in skillet. Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice (right from box).
Top with asparagus and turkey.
Cover skillet and simmer 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for five minutes and gradually stir in sugar.
Then add the rest of ingredients.
Spread in a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Sift powdered sugar and flour; set aside. In large bowl beat egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla, almond extract and salt on medium speed until soft peaks form.
Slowly add granulated sugar and keep beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in powdered sugar/flour mixture 1/2 cup at a time.
Turn into an ungreased angel food pan (10-inch tube pan).
Bake on lowest oven rack for about 40 minutes.
Cool cake in pan upside down.
When cool, loosen sides with knife and gently remove from pan.
Serves 12.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 3/4 cup of dry mix for filling.
In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, butter and egg; mix until crumbly.
Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar on low speed in mixer.
Add baking powder, soda, salt, water, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and flour. Turn mixer to medium speed and add carrots and pecans or black walnuts.
(Self-rising flour may be used but omit salt, soda and baking powder.)
Bake in 2 round 8-inch pans 35 minutes at 350° or bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan 40 minutes.

title: lite creamy spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise and seasonings; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetable dippers.

title: oyster pie
directions: Grease a round, 2-quart bowl casserole dish.
Layer Oysterette crackers and oysters; dot with margarine and add salt and pepper. Make two layers.
Pour half and half over all up to second layer. Let dish set for 20 minutes.
Top with some crushed saltines or Oysterettes.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box. Make two 9-inch layers and let cool.
Then split the two layers and make four layers. Put the icing between each layer.
Put cake in cover or wrap in foil and refrigerate for 2 days before cutting.
Keep refrigerated after cutting.
Good cake to freeze.

title: green bean bake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and one can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot through.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 10 servings.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until almost tender.
Drain; place in a large baking dish.
To this, add milk, flour and butter and mix thoroughly.
Add ham and mix well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 cup cheese and mix well.
Then top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: extra-special rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons of warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar, shortening, eggs, 1 cup warm water, salt and 2 cups flour.
Beat at low speed of an electric mixer 1 minute.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead 4 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape dough into a ball and place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and divide into 4 equal parts.
Roll each into a 12-inch circle on a floured surface; spread with butter.
Cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Roll up each wedge, beginning at wide end.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets point side down.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan; layer graham crackers.
In large bowl, combine pudding and milk and beat well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour half mixture over layered crackers, then add another layer on top and pour remaining mixture and layer again.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Layer on serving dish in order listed.
Serve with crackers. This is best made the day before serving.
It is pretty and very good.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix together and chill at least 2 hours.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Put the dry rice in the bottom of large baking dish or roaster.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the rice.
Lay chicken pieces on top of this.
Mix the 2 cans of soup and 1 can of water and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Cover with lid or foil.

title: sand dabs
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and water.
Mix into a very stiff dough with hands.
Add pecans.
Form into 1-inch logs and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes until only lightly brown.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Steam first 6 ingredients in as little water as possible until carrots and potatoes are tender.
Near the end of cooking, add peas, tomato puree and parsley.
Steam just until peas are tender, about 3 minutes.
Let stand, covered, a few minutes before serving.

title: velveeta cheese spread
directions: Take cheese out of refrigerator to soften a few hours before making. Whip the cheese with electric mixer. Add hard boiled eggs and pimentos, then mayonnaise and nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice in bottom of pan; pull chicken from bone and place on rice.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over rice and chicken.
Crush crackers; mix with poppy seed and sprinkle over chicken.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles in middle.

title: western style eggs
directions: Cut peppers in strips.
In large bowl with fork or whisk, beat eggs, water and pepper until mixed; set aside.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook red and green peppers in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil until tender.
With slotted spoon, remove peppers to bowl with egg mixture.
In same skillet, on high heat in 3 more tablespoons hot salad oil, cook mixture until it begins to set. With spatula, lift edge as it sets, tilting pan to allow uncooked portion to run under.
Crumble corned beef over egg mixture. Reduce heat to medium low; cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the powdered sugar, butter, vanilla and peanut butter together.
Shape into small balls.
Dip in Chocolate Glaze.
(Use a toothpick to dip the peanut butter balls.)
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: pate in aspic
directions: Add gelatin to consomme; stir until dissolved.
Heat slowly, add sherry and set aside to cool.
Pour consomme mixture about 3/4-inch deep into 3-cup mold that has been lightly oiled.
Put into refrigerator to congeal.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies or pound cake lengthwise; place in the bottom of bowl or pan.
Take juice of pineapple and pour over Twinkies.
Mix 2 cups of milk with pudding; spread over juice.
Take crushed pineapple; spread over pudding.
Take Cool Whip; spread over pineapple.
Place pecans over Cool Whip, if desired.

title: homemade marshmallows
directions: Mix granulated sugar with 3/4 cup water.
Simmer to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Place on large platter.
Pour hot syrup over softened gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Let stand until partially cooled; whip until thick and white and mixture will nearly hold its shape.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour into straight sided pans lined with equal parts of cornstarch and confectioners sugar mixed together.
Let stand in cool plate.
Cut with scissors and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: swiss cheese fondue
directions: Rub inside of fondue pan with garlic.
Put dish on heat and warm wine.
Add grated cheese, stirring constantly.
When mixture starts to bubble, add cornstarch mixed with Kirsch to a paste. Cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Have ready the plates and fondue forks for each guest and a basketful of bread cubes.
Have each guest spear a bread cube and dip in cheese mixture.
Cool slightly before eating.
Serves 5.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream 1/3 of powdered sugar with butter and salt in a large bowl.
Blend in vanilla, 2 tablespoons milk and remaining powdered sugar; mix well.
Gradually stir in remaining milk until desired spreading consistency is reached.
Makes enough frosting for 2 (9-inch) round pans.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip together Cool Whip and condensed milk with a fork until mixed.
Add drained cans of fruit cocktail, sliced peaches (cut up), pineapple, and mandarin oranges.
Stir.
Then stir in bananas (cut up or sliced) and 3 or 4 handfuls of marshmallows.
Extra bananas and or marshmallows may be added until salad is thick. Chopped walnuts may be added to top for decoration or put into salad but are not necessary.
Refrigerate.

title: choklit putting
directions: You buy it at the store.
Then put in a bole.
They you pore in some milk.
Then you stir it up.
Put it in the frig to save for later.

title: pasta with dried tomatoes and pesto
directions: Put chopped tomatoes into small bowl.
Cover with boiling water and let set for awhile until soft. Heat olive oil and butter in heavy skillet.
Add garlic and tomatoes with water to skillet. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes on high heat.
Add pesto sauce and stir well.
Use as a sauce over cooked spaghetti.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut up, cook and drain carrots.
Add all other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies with frankfurters
directions: Hush Puppy Mixture:
In bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add onion, buttermilk, then egg; blend. Dip bite size wieners into mixture and drop a few at a time into deep Crisco, heated to 375°.
Fry until golden and cooked through, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Insert toothpicks and serve hot, plain or with cheese sauce.

title: no-bake banana split cake
directions: Crush wafers and line the pan or casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine and dribble it over the wafers.
Mix together 2 melted sticks of margarine, eggs and the powdered sugar.
Beat mixture about 15 minutes.
Place the sliced bananas on the wafers; cover the bananas with crushed pineapple and pour egg mixture over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over top; sprinkle with pecans and garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: corn muffins
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together honey, eggs, egg whites, milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix with electric mixer at medium-high speed for 2 minutes.
Spray two muffin tins with cooking spray or line with baking cups.
Fill each cup 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes, or until tops are golden brown.

title: brussels sprouts with lemon mustard
directions: Trim Brussels sprouts and pull off any yellow or withered leaves.
Cut an X in the stem of each sprout.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and cool under cool running water.
Remove the leaves from sprouts and set aside.

title: sugar-free boiled custard
directions: Mix pudding and 1 quart milk.
Beat.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix in remainder of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix vanilla wafer crumbs with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Spread in pan, about 9 x 13-inch.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Prepare the day before.
Tear lettuce; place in serving bowl. Layer the vegetables and peas.
Spread mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise, then cheese on top of sugar. Refrigerate 15 to 24 hours.
Fry and crumble bacon; place on top of salad before serving.
To add color, chop tomato and place around edge of serving bowl.

title: tortilla chips
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, cornmeal and baking powder.
Mix in shortening with fork.
Stir in egg and water to form a stiff dough. Knead 5 minutes.
Divide into four equal parts.
Roll each into a 10-inch square, about 1/8-inch thick; cut into 2-inch squares. Divide each square into 2 triangles.
Fry in 1-inch hot oil (about 360°) for 2 minutes, or until golden on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with popcorn salt.
Store in airtight containers or plastic bags.

title: date nut roll
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Add
chopped, pitted dates and cook until mixture leaves sides and bottom of pan when stirred.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients and beat until thick.
Turn onto damp cloth and shape into roll.
Refrigerate.

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Bread eggplant slices, which have been pared and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Spread 2 tablespoons sauce in pan.
Layer 1/2 of eggplant, 1 can sauce, 1/2 oregano and 1/2 Mozzarella.
Repeat layers.
Place in oven and cook 25 minutes.
Add rest of Mozzarella and continue to cook 5 minutes until cheese is melted. Add hamburger as you layer the eggplant.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and place in 9 by 13-inch pan or large bowl.
Layer ingredients in order as given in recipe down and including carrots.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread on top as icing a cake.
Sprinkle bacon and grated cheese over all and cover.
Refrigerate 8 - 10 hours or overnight.
At serving time garnish with sliced tomatoes, if you like.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Crunch up noodles.
Layer the bottom of the casserole dish. Save a portion to top.
Mix ingredients together; fold in some noodles.
Cover top with leftover noodles.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom supreme
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1/4 butter.
Dissolve beef cubes in water. Melt 1/2 stick butter and blend in flour.
Add cream, salt, pepper and beef broth.
Top with cheese and bread crumb mixture before baking.
Bake in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salsa
directions: Blend ingredients to desired chunkiness.

title: martian salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with cottage cheese and pudding mix (do not make pudding; use dry mix).
Fold in Cool Whip; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chinese peanut butter sauce
directions: Blend the peanut butter and salad oil in a bowl. Add the remaining ingredients (except nuts) and mix well. This is good over chicken stir-fry.

title: chicken salad in toast cups
directions: Mix all real well, except bread and butter.
Cut 30 (2-inch) rounds of bread; butter both sides of bread.
Press into 1 3/4-inch muffin cups.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Fill each with 1 1/2 teaspoons chicken salad.

title: frozen cranberry salad(a country thanksgiving at the lamars)
directions: Spray PAM in desired mold.
Fold all ingredients together and pour into mold.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: pancakes(light, crisp and brown outside, moist and tender inside)
directions: Combine Quick Mix and sugar in a medium bowl. Mix well. Combine egg and milk or water in a small bowl.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Cook on a hot oiled griddle about 3 to 4 minutes, until browned on both sides.
Makes ten to twelve 4-inch pancakes.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar and eggs. Mix well. Add molasses and spices. Stir. Sift together flour and baking soda. Add alternately with coffee. Mix thoroughly. Add vinegar. Mix. Drop by spoonfuls onto well greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool and frost with icing sugar and milk.

title: mock sausage
directions: Mash peas.
Add salt, pepper and sage to flour.
Mix well. Add to mashed peas; mix and form into patties.
Fry in hot oil until browned.
A good, no cholesterol sausage.

title: crock pot mashed potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into crock pot.
Cook on low for 5 - 6 hours.
May be prepared 2 - 3 days in advance and refrigerated.

title: squash lemon pie
directions: Mix all in blender.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine coconut and margarine.
Press on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes.
Cool. In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then juice concentrate.
Stir in pineapple, rind and food coloring, if desired.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Cook and stir margarine, onion, salt and pepper together over medium heat until onion is slightly tender.
Blend in flour.	Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.	Stir in cheese until melted.
Place macaroni in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir cheese sauce into macaroni.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°. Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil hen until tender with enough water to make 1 1/2 quarts broth when done.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Combine popcorn and pecans in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix well and set aside.
Melt butter over low heat in a medium saucepan.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and salt; bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour syrup over popcorn mixture, stirring to coat.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring at 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight containers.

title: easy yeast muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Mix in sugar and Crisco.
Add flour. Stir yeast and water and pour into other ingredients.
Mix with a spoon. Grease muffin pan well. Fill 3/4 full with dough.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or as brown as you like. Store remaining dough in covered bowl in refrigerator.
It will keep for about a week.

title: mom's apple molasses bars
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in lemon rind, walnuts, raisins, cherries and applesauce.
Mix well.
Divide batter and put into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Cool and frost with buttercream frosting and sprinkle with candied cherries, chopped walnuts or silver shots as desired for Christmas.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix together.
Form small balls and press into small muffin tins.
Bake until done at 350°.
Fill with meat, fruit or dessert fillings.
Yields 24.

title: mexican honeymoon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls (1 teaspoon of dough).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll into powdered sugar 2 or 3 times.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: english lemon pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add extracts and salt.
Sift flour again and add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in a small bowl and add to the first mixture.
Blend well.
Bake in a 9-inch or 10-inch stem pan that has been greased and dusted with flour at 325° for about 1 hour and 5 minutes or until toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: potatoes plus
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Boil until tender.
Heat milk, add oleo, cheese and soup.
Drain potatoes and place in casserole dish. Sprinkle onions over.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: craig's party mix
directions: Melt butter and seasoning in large measuring cup.
Mix nuts, cereal and pretzels in a large roasting pan.
Pour melted butter mixture over cereal and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Simmer the onion in butter.
Add chicken; let simmer for a few more minutes.
Mix soup, rice, broth and soy sauce; put into dish. Put noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and flour and mix.
Stir in beaten eggs and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 300° until firm and brown.

title: chocolate lebkuchen(christmas chocolate bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift sugar.
Beat eggs until light. Add the sugar, gradually beating until well blended.
Grate and add chocolate.
Combine flour, cinnamon, cloves, allspice, baking soda and salt; sift.
Add sifted ingredients to egg mixture alternately with honey or molasses.
Add chopped ingredients. Spread dough with a spatula into two 9 x 13-inch greased pans. Bake about 20 minutes.
When cool, ice with chocolate icing or melted chocolate chips and decorate with blanched almonds.
Cut into bars.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine sugar and 4 cups water; heat until sugar dissolves. Add juice of 4 lemons and the grated rind of 1 lemon.
Add tea, almond extract and vanilla extract.
Add boiling water and serve hot.

title: coriander date cookies
directions: Chop nuts; set half aside.
Finely chop remaining nuts. Combine flour, salt, coriander and cinnamon.
Beat butter, sugar and zest until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in dates and coarsely chopped nuts.
Chill dough 30 minutes.
Form into logs about 2 inches in diameter, wrap in plastic and chill until firm but not hard, about 1 hour.
Roll logs of dough in finely chopped nuts.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges are golden.
Makes 54 cookies.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix altogether and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 300° or 350°.

title: herb filled croustades
directions: Cut 3-inch rounds from each slice of bread with a 3-inch plain or fluted cookie cutter; press carefully into well-buttered tiny muffin tins.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for about 10 minutes until slightly browned.
Fill with Mushroom Filling.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Roast chicken breast at 300° until cooked.
Allow to cool, then strip chicken.
Cut prunes, plums and apricots; add to chicken.
Add brown sugar, olive oil, salt and pepper; mix together.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order listed.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Drain pineapple. Beat the cream cheese until it is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup pecans; mix well.
Shape into a ball. Spread remaining 1/2 cup pecans on wax paper.
Roll balls in pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.

title: denver omelette scrambler
directions: In large non-stick skillet, prepare hash browns according to package directions. After turning once, sprinkle 2/3 cup cheese over potatoes. Transfer to a platter. In bowl, beat together eggs and milk. Add ham, chopped pepper, onion and remaining cheese. Add egg mixture to skillet. Cook over medium heat, sirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until eggs are set but still moist. Spoon egg mixture over center of hash browns. Serve with sour cream and salsa. This is great!

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Blend well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake cookies at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam. Cook onion and pepper in oleo until tender.
Blend in flour and milk; cook and stir constantly until thick.
Add salt and 1/2 of cheese, chicken, mushrooms, peas and pimentos.
Alternate layers of sauce and spaghetti.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400°
for 20 minutes.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix in beaten egg.
Add melted shortening, hot water and vanilla and mix well.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled and baked in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix soup mixes and mayo together. Defrost and drain water out of broccoli.
Roll broccoli inside chicken cutlets.
Cover with soup mix sauce over chicken cutlets. Sprinkle with grated cheese and then top with bread crumbs.
Bake for about 1 hour and 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve over rice. Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick peanut butter pie
directions: Cook vanilla pudding as directed on the box.
Add peanut butter and sugar.
May top with Cool Whip.

title: tuna divan casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until crisp-tender. Drain.
(Can also use chopped broccoli).
Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper; cook until bubbly.
Add milk all at once; cook and stir constantly until thick.
Add wine and cook 1 minute longer.
Add tuna.
Arrange broccoli in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over all; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco casserole
directions: Put chips on bottom of pan.
Then put hamburger (after cooked) and onion next.
Then layer chili beans, soup, Ro-Tel and then cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: onion pie
directions: Melt butter in a large frypan or Dutch oven; add onion and cook for 30 minutes on medium.
Stir often so as not to burn the onions.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop all ingredients; mix well.
Add salt and lemon juice.
DO NOT PROCESS OR BLEND!

title: pineapple angel rolls
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, butter and cinnamon in a small bowl, mixing well.
Spoon mixture evenly into 24 greased muffin cups. Roll Basic Angel Rolls dough into 1/2-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place a roll over pineapple mixture in each muffin cup.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 19 minutes or until rolls are golden brown.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Invert rolls onto serving platter and serve warm.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: beef with broccoli
directions: Brown pepper steak in deep frying pan with olive oil and garlic.
Remove meat and add onion.
Brown onion a little and add bag of broccoli with 1 cup water.
Add soy sauce and sugar.
Add another cup of hot water with flour and stir until thick.
Let simmer.
Add pepper steak and let cook another 10 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix
crushed
Oreo cookies and 1/2 cup melted margarine together; pat
into
a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Slice ice cream and put on the crumb crust.
Sprinkle salted peanuts on top and freeze.

title: vegetarian stew
directions: In saucepot coated with cooking spray, cook peppers, stirring, 10 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with flour and stir in yellow squash; cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and simmer, uncovered, 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jean's favorite brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Beat eggs well.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Mix in flour.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 20 brownies.

title: busy day oven beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in Dutch oven or baking dish.
Cover and cook in a 250° oven for at least 5 hours.
Three large potatoes may be cut up and added during the last hour or so of cooking, depending on the kind of potatoes used (new or old).

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill. Will keep well in the refrigerator.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover with pineapple and juice.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Top with coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Heat egg whites on warm while mixing cake.
Just before you add nuts, stir in egg whites in cake and then add nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken mulligan
directions: Boil hen with proper seasoning until tender.
Debone hen, saving broth.
In the broth cook lemon, hot peppers, tomatoes, onions, garlic, celery, bell pepper, sugar, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper until vegetables are done.
Add mushroom soup and thickening made of 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup water.
Simmer until thickened.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix with mixture.
Add diced meat.
Simmer for about 30 minutes before serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine and add peaches.
Add lemon extract and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine beef, soup, crumbs, milk and egg.
Brown and pour off fat.
Add flour in skillet and brown.
Add remainder of soup in water.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.

title: chicken velveeta spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Save 1 quart of broth.
Add all ingredients to broth, except cheese, peas and chicken.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Blend in cheese.
When melted, add peas and chicken. Season to taste.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: tasty easy dessert
directions: Layer items in order given.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Beat egg, sugar and milk together. Add flour, salt and baking powder (all sifted together).
Beat well and add vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto oiled baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spray 7x12 dish with cooking spray.
Layer crackers, 1/2 pudding mixture, crackers, remaining pudding.
Microwave frosting until pourable and then pour over all.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Can be made two days ahead.

title: fruit sauce for pineapple and banana salad
directions: Cut up bananas.
Cook flour, sugar, salt, egg and juice on medium heat until thick; remove from stove and cool.
When completely cool, stir into bananas and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator and when cool and ready to serve, grate cheese on top.
A little lemon juice on bananas keeps them from turning dark.

title: easy holiday punch
directions: Add gelatin to 2 cups boiling water in a large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen juices.
Stir until well blended. Add 6 cups cold water and pineapple juice; mix well.
Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 50 servings.

title: macaroni soup
directions: Put everything in a large saucepan except macaroni.
Cook for about 5 min. Then add desired amount of macaroni.
Cook till macaroni is done.
Add about 1 c. sweet cream and heat thoroughly. Enjoy.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Spray a 3-quart Pyrex dish with Pam.
Layer beans, meat, chilies and cheese. Drizzle taco sauce on top.
Garnish with sour cream.
Slice thin avocado on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: deer meat stew
directions: Brown meat and onions in small amount of butter; add meat tenderizer, pepper, bay leaves and tomato paste.
Add water according to desired consistency.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 2 to 3 hours, or until meat is tender.
After meat is tender, add vegetables; continue simmering until vegetables are done.
Add regular salt after stew is done if needed.

title: classic chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt butter, blend in flour.
Add broth. Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in sherry, salt and nutmeg. Keep warm.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch serving dish, spread bean dip on sides and bottom. Combine avocados (mashed), lemon juice, salt, pepper and mayonnaise. Place this mixture on top of bean dip in the bottom only of dish.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Place this mixture on top of avocado mixture. Top in this order: cheese, green onion, tomatoes and black olives. Serve with corn chips.

title: spiced applesauce bread
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients and spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Mix and sprinkle last 3 ingredients over dough and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: bran raisin muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and mix in sugar and raisins. Add the beaten egg with the sour cream.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°, until brown.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix water with butter.
Add sugar.
Let stand until warm.
Add egg.
Mix yeast in a small amount of water; add to other ingredients.
Add flour.
Salt to taste.
Knead 2 or 3 minutes. Let double in bulk, then punch down.
Make out into buns; let rise again.
Bake at 350° or until brown.
Brush with butter before baking.

title: bread(2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in sugar and salt.
Add about 1/2 of the flour and mix well.
Add the egg and stir in well.
Then add the shortening.
Mix well for 2 minutes.
Add the rest of the flour.
Mix well and form a ball.
Cover with grease.

title: cabbage plate
directions: Simmer until tender about 15 minutes. Delicious carrots and color and no onion taste.

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Melt margarine.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix together with pretzels and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Add thawed Cool Whip.
Beat together and pour over cooled crust. Dissolve 2 small packages strawberry jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries to jello.
Put in refrigerator until it sets a little.
Pour over Cool Whip mixture and refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: double peach twirl
directions: Peel and puree peaches adding 1 cup nectar until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients; blend until smooth and garnish with peach slices and mint sprigs.
Makes 4 cups.

title: lemon cream pie(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer until well blended.
Pour into a cooked 9-inch pie crust.
Cook in microwave (High, 700 watts) for about 5 minutes.
Check after 4 minutes; mixture should be firm.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in two 9-inch deep uncooked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Put dry ingredients together; then add wet ingredients.
Spoon teaspoon of cookie dough on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
You will probably want to double this recipe.

title: christmas breakfast casserole
directions: Add enough milk to bread cubes to moisten.
Cut bacon into tiny pieces and brown until crisp; drain and set aside.
Beat eggs and seasonings and pour into a heavy buttered skillet and stir as for scrambled eggs.
When nearly done, add cubed bread and milk mixture and cook a little longer.
Into buttered casserole dish, layer egg mixture, then Swiss cheese, then crumbled bacon until all used up.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Bake, covered, in 275° to 325° oven until cheese melts.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and skin. Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Drain Veg-All; place Veg-All and chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan, bring to boil the broth and soup; pour over chicken and Veg-All. In another bowl, combine flour, salt, pepper, buttermilk and margarine; mix thoroughly to form batter.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: summer dessert pizza
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar;
beat in egg and extracts.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes. Press dough into a greased 12 in. or 14 in. pizza pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-14 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely,
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Add whipped topping, mix well.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on top.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve sugar into 3 cups water; bring to boil for 7 minutes.
Steep tea in a cup of boiling water about 7 minutes. Cool, then dilute orange juice as directed on can.
Combine sugar, syrup, tea and juices.
Put equal amounts into 2 (1 gallon) glass jars.
Refrigerate.
When ready to use, place in punch bowl and add 1 quart ginger ale to each and plenty of ice.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Can be made several days before use.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered and 15 minutes more uncovered.
Can be made a day ahead of needed time.
Refrigerate uncooked.
Can add, if desired, mushrooms, green peppers, onions, ham, etc.
Great for breakfast.

title: chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, butter and milk until they come to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Spread 1 cup sauce over bottom of a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with 3 noodles in a single layer, 1 cup Ricotta, 2/3 cup Mozzarella, 1/3 cup Parmesan and 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Repeat with a second layer.
Top with remaining noodles, then the sauce and Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Cover lightly with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High, 6 to 8 minutes; rotate dish 1/2 turn. Reduce power to Medium.
Microwave 30 to 32 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn once until noodles are tender.
Shield corners of dish with foil if noodles begin to overcook.
Let stand covered 5 to 10 minutes to equalize temperature and for easier cutting.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buried treasure muffins
directions: Grease muffin tin or line with paper muffin cups.
Stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Dig a small hole in the middle of it all.
In another bowl break egg and mix with the milk and oil.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture (pour it into the hole) and stir until mixed.
Don't stir too long, leave it lumpy.
Now add whatever goes inside:
With fruit, coconut or grated Cheddar cheese; mix these in with the batter, then pour into muffin tin until 3/4 full.
With jam:
Fill muffin tin 1/2 full, then add 1 teaspoon of jam in the center, then add a teaspoon more of batter or more to completely cover the jam. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: fluffy salad(make this recipe the day before you need it.)
directions: Drain and cut up peaches, saving 1/4 cup peach syrup.
Beat syrup and cream cheese or salad dressing together.
Fold in fruits and marshmallows.
Whip your topping and fold into fruit mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and onion together.
Add chicken and rice and put in casserole dish.
Crumble corn flakes; mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix sugar, salad oil, vinegar and salt to make dressing.
Add vegetables.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: fat-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray. In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed.
(Optional:
You can add 1/2 cup raisins at this time.) Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes or until firm.
Do not overbake.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: big chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the flour, cocoa, soda, sugar and salt.
Add shortening, sour milk and 2 eggs.
Beat well.
Add hot water and vanilla.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: quiche lorraine(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place bacon, cheese and onion in pie shell.
Combine eggs, cream and seasonings.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, butter, syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir well and then pour over popped corn and peanuts.
Spread over a cookie sheet.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel, then cut potatoes into wedges.
Cook until tender in unsalted water.
Chop onion.
Cut red pepper into strips.
Saute ground beef in 1 tablespoon butter until it loses its pinkness. Add onion, pepper, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Add vinegar, parsley and bay leaf.
Cook for a few minutes.
Transfer to lightly greased baking dish.

title: practically foolproof meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until peaks form.
Gradually add marshmallow cream.
Spread over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: rice with chicken
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil while coating chicken with 1 tablespoon of oil, salt, garlic, oregano and paprika.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm beer.
Add flour and mix; knead for 10 minutes.
Let rise, covered, in warm place for 1 hour until doubled.
Shape and place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle on coarse salt.
Bake at 475° until brown, approximately 12 minutes.

title: taco (5 can) casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and peppers.
Combine all 5 canned products in saucepan and heat.
Pour into hamburger mixture.

title: classic pavlova
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until starts to stiffen.
Add 2 tablespoons of the superfine sugar at a time.
Beat about 2 minutes between each addition.
Mix the 1/4 cup granulated sugar with the cornstarch.
Continue beating egg white mixture and add this mixture.
When forms stiff peaks, add lemon juice and fold in with rubber spatula.
Pour about 3/4 (perhaps a little less) of the meringue into an aluminum pie pan that measures 7 inches at inside bottom and has been lined with aluminum foil.
Spread evenly over bottom and sides.
Pour remaining meringue into an aluminum pie pan that measures 6 inches at inside bottom and has been lined with aluminum foil.
Spread evenly over bottom and sides.
Place pans on a cookie sheet and bake meringue in a 300° oven that has been preheated.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until meringue shell is well browned.
Let cool in oven after oven has been turned off, about 5 minutes.

title: carne adovado
directions: Combine all the spices in a jar and add about a cup of water and shake up. Then pour on the meat in a baking dish. Then add flour
and water to the jar, shake and stir into meat. Add more water if necessary and marinate overnight.

title: glaze for fresh coconut cake
directions: Combine sugar, coconut milk, vinegar and butter in a saucepan. Cook to a clear syrup; it will be very thin.
Add half of the coconut.
Pour mixture onto hot cake.
Sprinkle the rest of the coconut onto the glazed cake.

title: tomato beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak across grain into thin strips (easier if the meat is partially frozen).
After cutting, bring steak to room temperature for better browning.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, add
oil,
then
mix in the dry ingredients. Add the apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: german chocolate angel pie
directions: Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar and beat until foamy.
Add sugar, two tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition until all is well blended. Continue beating until mixture stands in a stiff peak.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sweet and spicy chicken wings
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside 1/4 cup for dipping.
Marinate chicken wings at least 1 hour in mixture. Broil 5 minutes on each side, until chicken is cooked and glazed. Serve with dipping sauce.

title: quiche
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put into bottom of pie shell and cover with cheese.
Add apple and lemon juice.
Beat eggs and add cream and pour into pie shell covering ingredients.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: cabbage marinara
directions: Saute ground beef until no longer pink. Add chopped onion and cook another 5 minutes. Stir in seasonings.

Spread 3 cups shredded cabbage in 2-quart baking dish. Cover with meat mixture and top with remaining 3 cups cabbage. Pour undiluted tomato soup over top. Cover and bake in a 350° oven until cabbage is tender (about 1 hour). Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in large casserole dish or deep bowl. In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Marinate for 4 hours.
Barbecue or grill until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: In medium bowl, with fork, beat the cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in crushed pineapple.
(The secret to this ball is to drain pineapple and squeeze between paper towels until it is so dry as to have no moisture at all.)
Stir in 1 cup of pecans, then green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into a ball; roll in remaining nuts (1 cup). Wrap in plastic wrap or foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with pineapple slices, cherries and parsley.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°, or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: no fault pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, shortening and salt.
Mix water, vinegar and egg together.
Add to flour mixture.
Makes 1 double pie crust.

title: viennese velvet
directions: *Note:
To make double strength coffee, use regular amount of grounds but half the water

title: parmesan zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini with butter in water about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with seasonings and cheese.

title: feather fowlie
directions: Skin and joint the chicken. Soak in salted water for 30 minutes. Drain and wash.
Put in a stew pan with the ham, the sliced vegetables, thyme, mace, parsley,
stalks and water. Season.
Simmer gently for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until the bird is tender. Strain into a clean pan. Remove any grease. Add the meat from the fowl, minced.
