Heat for 15 minutes.
Add extra white stock, if necessary, during this time. Draw the pan aside. Add the beaten egg yolks and the cream. Stir carefully into the soup. Heat to cook the eggs slightly, but do not boil.
Test the seasoning. Add the parsley just before serving. Some people add only the white part of the meat and serve the rest as a separate dish.

title: miss gertrude's pie
directions: Bake pie crusts according to instructions on the pie crust bag. (Or you may use graham cracker pie crusts.)
Mix together in bowl 1 can Eagle Brand milk, juice of 1 lemon and 1 large can "drained" crushed pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.
(I like to add food coloring to Cool Whip, depending on the occasion or time of year!)

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine milk, salt, shortening and molasses.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast to cooled milk.
Allow to stand 5 minutes. Add raisins.
Add flour, a little at a time, beating well after each addition, until dough is just stiff enough to knead on a lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover with a warm, damp cloth, and allow to double in size.
Knead down; allow to double again.
Form in loaves.
Place in well-oiled pans. Cover and let rise until double.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Cut up (leave skins on potatoes and carrots).
Put in Dutch oven.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender. Puree vegetables and water in blender.
Return to pan.
Add Velveeta cheese (cubed).
Stir until melted.
Add 1 to 2 cups milk.
Keep warm.
Don't boil.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large punch bowl.
Serves 35.

title: raisin creme dream
directions: Mix raisins and water; cook low for 5 or so minutes (until soft).
Add milk, sugar, egg yolks, flour and cinnamon; mix well. Cook on medium heat until thick (sticks easily).
Pour into crust. Beat egg whites and sugar until fluffy and pour over pie as a glaze before baking in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Mix and boil margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter.
Mix together and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Chill until cool.
Makes 38 to 40 cookies.

title: better for you burger
directions: Heat pint of vegetable oil to about 175°.
Add hamburger and stir until meat juice begins to boil.
Cook and stir with the juice barely bubbling for 10 more minutes while breaking up the meat.
Put the meat and oil into strainer and save the liquid. Next pour a cup or two of boiling water over the meat in the strainer and save the water with the rest of the liquid.
Put the liquid in the refrigerator for 1 hour, then skim off the hardened fat.
Pour the rest of fat free liquid over the meat.
The meat is ready for any dish that requires ground beef.

title: husband's casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together; set aside.
Boil noodles or cook rice.
Brown hamburger, add onion, salt, garlic, salt and tomato sauce.
Pepper or other appropriate spices may also be added.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Mix together the crab, shrimp, celery, green pepper, onion and pimento.
Mix together separately the sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Combine 2 mixtures; stir together and place in deep casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine ingredients and store in airtight container.
Add 2 rounded teaspoonfuls (adjust for your taste) per cup of hot water.

title: strawberries in chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add oil.
Dip tip of strawberry in chocolate. Place on wax paper until firm.

title: strawberries elegante
directions: Rinse strawberries and drain thoroughly.
You may remove caps or leave them on for color.
Mix together yogurt, brown sugar and vanilla.
Spoon yogurt mixture into middle of dessert plate or bowl.
Arrange strawberries around yogurt.
Dip strawberries in yogurt mixture before eating.

title: mix-easy party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Combine chilled juices; add sugar syrup.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Place ice in large punch bowl; add punch.
Garnish.
Makes approximately 62 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Place broccoli in casserole.
Top with slices of chicken.
Combine other ingredients except bread crumbs. Pour over chicken.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: In skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add chicken and cook until browned on both sides.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
In same skillet, cook mushrooms over high heat, stirring occasionally, until all liquid has evaporated.
Sprinkle mushrooms with flour and stir quickly to combine.
Gradually stir in water. Add orange juice, orange sections and broth.
Mix and stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add chicken and let simmer for 3 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, bacon and broccoli in just enough water to cover them.
When potatoes are done, remove the bacon.
Do not drain. Pour in desired amount of milk to make soup.
Add the Velveeta, shredded or thinly sliced.
Salt and pepper.
If soup needs thickening, stir in a few potato flakes.
Do not boil!

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Bake covered ribs at 425° for 30 minutes.
Bring sauce ingredients to a boil.
Pour over ribs.
Bake 45 minutes longer, basting evenly.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: karen's favorite coffee streusel cake
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the flour, sugar, coffee, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, vanilla, shortening, egg and milk.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan, floured at bottom.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: best goop ever
directions: Fry ground beef with onion until browned.
Cook noodles; drain.
Stir cheese into hot noodles.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Add ground beef mixture, green pepper, milk, olives and soup.
Mix well.
Top with bread crumbs or crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put in casserole and bake, uncovered, until it begins to bubble at 350°.

title: mexican fiesta casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Cook 5 minutes on High.
Layer in 2-quart casserole dish:
1/2 crumbled ground beef, 1/2 onion, 1/2 soup and tomato mixture and 1/2 cheese, in that order, Repeat, ending with cheese.
Cook about 12 minutes on Roast.

title: candy apples
directions: Combine ingredients, stir continuously over medium heat until boiling.
Cook until hard crack stage 280°.
Remove from heat; dip apples, place on buttered platter (if weather is very humid, candy will stay sticky).

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix; put in pie shell.
Bake at moderate temperature until toothpick comes out clean.

title: kickin' chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Add sour cream before serving.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown and drain meat.
In a large pan, put in all ingredients. Simmer over low heat for 45 minutes.

title: mon-doo(korean egg rolls)
directions: Brown meat, onions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons sesame seed oil.
Season according to taste with soy sauce and garlic powder. Place a small amount into the middle of egg roll wrapper.
Roll and seal wrapper by wetting finger with a little water (egg roll wrappers will seal tight).
Fry egg rolls in sesame seed oil or deep fry.
Can be frozen and microwaved when needed.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Stir in 1/2 cup hot water.
Beat in egg yolks and add another 1/2 cup hot water.
Cook in a double boiler until thick, stirring often.
Remove from heat; add margarine and stir until melted.
When cool, put into a cooked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown in oven.
Meringue may be omitted and served with Cool Whip.

title: cold zucchini soup
directions: In a saucepan, simmer zucchini, green pepper, onion and chicken stock.
Place sour cream (or substitute), parsley and dill in a blender; add the simmered vegetables and blend for 30 seconds.
Add the remaining stock and blend until it has a nice consistency.
Chill thoroughly.

title: easy fudge
directions: Thin milk in microwave or top of double boiler until hot.
Add chocolate chips.
Melt in milk, stirring constantly and microwave 30 more seconds.
Add nuts.
Stir.
Pour in buttered 6 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Refrigerate.
Slice when firm.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Melt cream cheese in tomato soup, then add other ingredients. Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: easy corn soup
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Saute onion and celery until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and place over medium or low heat until hot.

title: john's apple cake(from john kram's bakery back in 1930)
directions: In a bowl, combine well the apples and 1/4 cup of the sugar. Add the cinnamon.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer, combine the oil and the 1 3/4 cups of sugar and beat for 2 minutes.
Add eggs.
In a bowl, sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the flour mixture to the oil and add orange juice and beat in the vanilla.
Pour 1/3 of the batter into a buttered and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Arrange 1/2 the apple mixture over it.
Pour half the remaining apple mixture.
Bake the cake on 350° for 50 minutes to an hour.
Let the cake cool for 10 minutes.

title: southern pilau
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Add onion and rice to bacon dripping in skillet.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes, until rice is transparent. Spoon the skillet mixture and other ingredients into a casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: microwave cashew crunch
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil, lightly buttered.
In an 8-cup microwave-safe measuring cup or bowl, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir.
Add cashews; blend well.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 or 4 1/2 minutes or until mixture is light brown; stir in butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add baking soda; stir quickly to blend.
Pour immediately into prepared cookie sheet; quickly spread with wooden spoon.
Cool 30 minutes.
Break into pieces; store in airtight container.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix & store in large container with lid.
Use 1/3 c. to 1 c. hot water.

title: fuhrman fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Drain other cans of fruit (don't save juice).
Combine all fruits in large bowl.
In large measuring cup, combine yogurt, honey and pineapple juice.
Pour sauce over fruit; toss gently.
Chill.

title: orange roughy marsala
directions: In large skillet, pour a small amount of olive oil and heat. Sprinkle orange roughy with salt and lemon pepper.
Place in skillet.
As fish melts, pour off liquid and discard.
Turn fish over; sprinkle again with lemon pepper and salt.
Pour wine over and cook until wine disappears.
Turn fish to brown on both sides (approximately 10 minutes).

title: peach glazed stuffed pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain and dice peaches, reserving syrup. Mix contents of vegetable/seasoning packet (from cornbread stuffing mix), water and margarine in a bowl.
Stir in crumbs, peaches and reserved syrup.
Fill pork chops pockets with stuffing.

title: apple torte(epleterte)
directions: Set out a 9-inch pie pan.
Measure 1 1/4 cups sifted flour into a bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup softened butter with a pastry blender or 2 knives until well blended.
Cover and set aside overnight (in a cool place but not the refrigerator).
The next day, cut in 1/2 cup softened butter with a pastry blender until well blended.
Add 6 tablespoons sifted flour and blend thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator.
Put into a 3-quart heavy saucepan the apples and water.
Cook over medium heat 30 minutes.
Stir in 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Cool completely.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Melt margarine; add lemon juice, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook chicken on grill and baste continuously until chicken is done, about 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Put the tomatoes, beans and chili powder in pan and heat. While this is heating, fry hamburger, onion, salt and pepper until done. Add to tomato mixture. Simmer until hot and flavored. If not soupy enough, add a little water.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix together pecans and coconut and put in a 9 x 13 pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut/nut.
Mix together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix and drop by spoonfuls over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: In bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half the mixture over pecan mixture.
Mix the powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo. Drop clumps over the cake mixture.
Spread remaining mixture over cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend salt, pepper, paprika and sugar.
Add garlic, catsup, water and mustard.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, butter and lemon juice.
Stir to blend.
May use as a sauce over chicken, pork or beef.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir until mixed and blended.
Pour into a buttered, 8-inch square pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: barbecue ribs or chicken(oven baked)
directions: Soak ribs in a mixture of water and liquid smoke for about 2 hours.
Remove from mixture and sprinkle lightly with seasonings and tenderizer.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake slowly in oven at about 300°.
Cook chicken about 2 hours and pork ribs about 3 hours or until tender.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine jello, water and pie filling.
Let set.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple and spread over top of jello.
Let set 2 hours.

title: make ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Add to other ingredients.
Put in an 8 x 12-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Nice for company.

title: coconut cake
directions: Flour and grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake by directions on box and bake.
While cake is baking, mix sugar and sour cream together.
Remove cake from oven.
While hot, frost with sour cream-sugar mixture.
Poke knife into cake at random.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Serve hot or cold.
Better the next day.

title: arch cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs, flour and soda together well. Add chopped apples, then coconut and nutmeats.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This is very good.

title: texas caviar(appetizer)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour on salad dressing and marinate two hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ham and cheese sandwich puff
directions: Combine ham, cheese, mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread on 6 slices of toast.
Place remaining slices on top to make 6 sandwiches.
Cut sandwiches diagonally in quarters.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, stand the quarters on edge, crust side down.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat softened cream cheese, then add sugar and mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip. Let set 10 minutes or longer in refrigerator.
Smooth over cooled pretzel crust.
Add boiling water to jello and stir until jello is dissolved.
Break strawberries apart and add to jello.
Pour over first layer.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Make into small patties and place on waxed paper.
Let set until dry.
More powdered sugar can be added to make stiff.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Separate eggs; beat yolks and add to creamed mixture.
Add sifted flour and baking powder, then milk and vanilla.
Use mixer to beat egg whites.
Fold them into other ingredients and then mix all together.
Pour into cake pan (13 x 11 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Test with toothpick in center of cake at end of baking time.
It's done when toothpick is dry.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix by hand the sugar, eggs and oil. Add the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Stir and add apples and walnuts.
Bake in small loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, sugar, salt, drained crushed pineapple, bananas pieces and enough red color to give pink tint. Lightly fold in nuts and Bing cherries.
Spoon into paper muffin cups (large) which have been placed in muffin pans.
Freeze.
Take from freezer 15 minutes before serving. Remove paper.
Serve on lettuce.

title: red waldorf cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat until well blended.
Mix flour, salt and cocoa.
Stir into sugar mixture. Fold in chopped nuts.
Spread evenly in an 11 1/2 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Whil still hot, ice.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together the oleo and sugar.
Add to creamed mixture the eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and lemon extract and beat well.
Add candied cherries, candied pineapple and pecans.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in a large pan or 3 loaf pans at 250° until done. Bake for 3 hours at 250° if using one large pan or 325° for loaf pans.
Grease and flour pans well.
Serve with no frosting.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches, or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg slightly; stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened. Pour batter into cups.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 17 minutes. Makes 12.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into ungreased 9x13 pan.

title: alaskan sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (15 x 10-inch) jelly roll pans.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except the ice cream.
Mix and pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt, sugar and baking powder and stir in eggs (beaten slightly), milk and oil.
Mix well.
Add corn and remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onions, green pepper, cauliflower, carrots, celery and pimiento in a large glass bowl; sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Cover; let stand about 2 hours.
Drain and rinse in cold water; drain well.
Pack vegetables in hot pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet, pinching and sealing edges together. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix together cream cheese, Hidden Valley dressing mix and mayonnaise. Spread on crescent rolls. Top with any or all toppings.

title: a sheepherder's dip
directions: Cut 5 or 6 inches off top of bread.
Pull out soft insides (save for making bread dressing).
Soften cream cheese.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Fill shell with mixture.
Replace top of bread; cover with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Use fresh vegetables as well as top of bread for dippers.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Mix sugar, oil, egg and orange juice.
Add baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Mix well and drop in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° until well done.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Put 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, celery, onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix butter with Ritz cracker crumbs, then top casserole.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and chill.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, coconut, dates and nuts.
Cook over medium-high heat for 6 minutes and cool for 1 minute.
Add Rice Krispies; mix well, then let cool.
Roll in little balls and then in powdered sugar.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Brown ribs in heavy skillet, then arrange in a deep baking dish.
Cover with onion slices.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over onion.
Cover and bake at 325° until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini and set aside.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to the zucchini mixture; stir thoroughly until combined.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on pans for 2 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Cookies are cake like.
Yields 3 dozen.
Can be frozen in airtight containers and thawed as needed.

title: zucchini italian style
directions: Saut 1 sliced onion in margarine until yellow.
Add one pound of zucchini, sliced, and cook and stir 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup of fresh or canned tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and cook until tender (25 minutes) or put in a casserole dish and sprinkle grated cheese and bake at 375 degrees until brown.
Serves 4.

title: no-bake fresh peach cobbler
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine 1/4 cup of sugar, cornstarch, salt and water.
Stir to dissolve, then cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add remaining sugar and butter; return to heat and cook until sugar dissolves.
Add vanilla and peaches.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan, a pie pan or individual serving dishes.
Top with granola.
Serve with cream, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and salt into bowl.
Add margarine; mix with pastry blender.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs.
Add egg and milk to remaining mix.
Add vanilla.
Sprinkle with the cup of crumbs, then nuts and shaved candy bars.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Candy bars will ice cake.)

title: beans deluxe
directions: Cook onions in bacon grease; add to pork and beans. Add additional ingredients and put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: rohliky(crescent rolls)
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water with a teaspoon of sugar. Combine hot milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm. Add 1 cup of the flour; add yeast and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in remaining flour, enough to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead lightly 5 to 8 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Divide dough into thirds.
Roll each to a 9-inch circle.
At this point, you can brush circle with melted butter and spread Solo brand almond filling on top.

title: taco-filled peppers
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roast beef french dip sandwiches
directions: Rub roast with oil. Rub in remaining ingredients.
Put in open pan and bake at 325° to desired doneness.
Put a pan of water on lower rack of oven and keep full during baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Mix together the eggs, margarine, mayonnaise, soup, onion and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Add broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top, along with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chiligetti
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and beans (with liquid).
Cook, uncovered, about 10 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; add onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and rice. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking to skillet. Pour this mixture into a 4-quart casserole; add seasoning packets from the rice boxes.
Mix well.
Pour the dissolved bouillon cubes and water into this mix.
Cook, covered, in a 400° oven for about 1 hour or until all liquid is absorbed.
This is delicious with turkey or any meats, alone or with gravy served with it.
My family enjoyed it served at Christmas dinner with gravy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly by hand.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning, onion and tomatoes to ground beef.
Line 9 x 13-inch dish with tortilla shells, after spraying bottom with Pam.
Add ground beef mixture.
Add another layer of shells.
Mix cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and eggs together.
Pour on top of second tortilla layer.
Slice a fresh tomato on top and sprinkle a little more cheese on it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and guacamole.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Arrange a layer of wafers in a baking dish.
Slice bananas and layer on top of wafers. Spread the pudding over the bananas.
Continue in layers until all is used.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add Sweet 'N Low and vanilla, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue over pudding. Bake at 425° until meringue is lightly browned.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with the rolls and press the perforations together.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool. Prepare filling by combining cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread on crust.
Add vegetables and cheese on top. Serve in 2 x 2-inch pieces.

title: no-roll pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Pour into pie plate. Spread out to saucer shape.
Mix oil and milk.
Pour into flour mixture and mix all together.
Shape into pie plate with fingers. Flute edges.
If used for a filled pie, prick with fork and bake at 425 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients and mix well. Add chopped nuts. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove and sprinkle with marshmallows. Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: a+ fruit salad
directions: In serving bowl, carefully combine pineapple, oranges, apples, bananas and marshmallows.
In medium saucepan, beat eggs well; add sugar and beat until blended.
Add juices and mix well.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Chill.
Drain liquid from fruit mixture; fold whipped cream into dressing mixture and stir into fruit thoroughly.

title: pineapple frozen salad
directions: Dissolve 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup water and 1 can crushed pineapple.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Mix lemon jello with hot ingredients and put in freezer until becomes pretty thick.
Then add Cool Whip and grated cheese.
Freeze.

title: chili-cheese dip(crock-pot)
directions: Brown ground beef well and drain off all grease.
Put ground beef and all remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well. Cover and cook on high for an hour, stirring until cheese is fully melted.

title: potatoes with mushrooms
directions: Place layer of potatoes sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add layer of onions and bell pepper.
Repeat until casserole is filled.
Mix soup and milk.
Put in about 1/2 stick of margarine. Pour mushroom mixture over potatoes and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours (or until tender).

title: kaye's salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Blend in Miracle Whip and cottage cheese.
Dump in pineapple and Milnot.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate.
This is a great sugar-free salad.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in rice.
Lay on chicken, cut up on top.
Add onion soup mix.
Mix water with soups and add with chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: flora raper's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until done.
Remove from broth. Cool and remove chicken from bones.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Divide into 3 balls.
Roll out with rolling pin and cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Bring broth to a boil.
Drop in squares one at a time.
Add chicken and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: low-fat corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, flour and sugar with Egg Beaters.
Stir in milk, corn, salt and pepper.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake in a pan of water until firm in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Can be doubled.
I use Egg Beaters and canned evaporated skim milk to cut down on fat.

title: dad's casserole(8 servings)
directions: Prepare frozen noodles in accordance with package directions. Brown ground beef and onion.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese, tomato sauce, sugar and salt.
Add to cooked ground beef; combine with noodles.
Place in greased casserole dish; top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: make your own baking powder(free of sodium aluminum sulphate)
directions: Sift together 8 times and store in tightly covered container. Refrigerate if to be stored very long.
Use as you would regular baking powder.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Mix all ingredients and cook slowly for a couple of hours or more.
May be frozen.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix 11 egg yolks and 1 whole egg plus 1/2 egg shell of water in large mixing bowl.
Stir with 2 fingers.
Add a pinch of salt.
Add flour a little at a time until not sticky but not too stiff.
Once you can make a ball out of it, cut in 4. Roll 1 piece; cut into squares.
Stack, flouring between each.
Cut thin into noodles. Separate noodles in lots of flour.
Let dry; freeze after dried.

title: quick fried rice
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute 1 cup chopped vegetables in the oil until tender-crisp.
Add brown rice, cayenne pepper, sesame oil and soy sauce.
Stir until heated through.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Grease bottom of rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch with oil. Mix Parmesan cheese, flour, Italian seasoning, paprika and pepper. Coat chicken.
Arrange, skin sides down, in pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Turn chicken; divide chili sauce to cover all pieces. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until melted, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: pepperoni squares
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Slowly add dry ingredients.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into a greased square baking pan.
Sprinkle chopped pepperoni over batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: pork chops with onion rice
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Spread rice in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Reserve 1 tablespoon dry onion soup mix.
Sprinkle remaining mix over rice.
Pour hot water over rice.
Arrange chops on top of rice mixture and sprinkle reserved onion soup mix over chops.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix ingredients together and then spread in a 9 x 14-inch pan. In a double boiler pan, melt 1 package milk chocolate chips. Spread melted chocolate chips on top.
Cut before freezing. Freeze for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
A few cut up wieners can be added or 2 slices of bacon.
Bake, covered, for about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix one slightly beaten egg with dry cake mix and melted butter to a moist dough consistency.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press mixture evenly in pan.
Soften cream cheese and beat with electric mixer with remaining eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in powdered sugar gradually; beat until smooth (this takes several minutes).
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
The cheese mixture sinks into center and leaves a firmer crust at edges.
Cut into squares to serve.
Great sprinkled with powdered sugar, pecans and/or strawberries.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions; cool completely and split layers.
Combine frozen coconut, sour cream and sugar.
Set aside 1 cup.
Spread mix over split layers.
Mix together Cool Whip and reserved coconut mix and spread over top and sides. Refrigerate 3 days in airtight container.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry fizz
directions: In a blender, combine ingredients. Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into tall glasses.
Slowly pour beverage down side of glasses to fill. Stir gently up and down. Serve immediately.

title: dovard's zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger dip
directions: Brown meat in skillet;
drain.
Reduce heat to low.
Add Velveeta, milk, mustard and catsup;
stir until Velveeta is melted.
Serve hot with French fries or tortilla chips.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate bits and butter; cool slightly.
Then add marshmallows and chopped nuts.
Shape into roll.
Then roll in chopped coconut or crushed nuts.
Wrap in foil; cool.
Cut into slices with sharp knife.
Serves 16.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: Begin by making pastry as follows:
Sift flour with salt, also sugar.
Fold in 2/3 cup of shortening and slowly add enough cold water to form a stiff paste.

title: easy-time holiday squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
At medium speed, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
At low speed, add flour and lemon extract.
Pour batter into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Mark off into 20 squares or more.
Place 1 spoonful pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, egg yolks and sugar.
Crumble crackers and add hot milk.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken salad or casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(Uncooked great for stuffed tomato salad.)
For casserole, fill 9x13 dish.
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs or slivered almonds.
Best if refrigerated overnight.	Bake 40-45 minutes at 325°.
Freezes well!
Serves 10.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle on top of poured mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: aram's cutout sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, margarine,
sugar,
eggs and flavorings.
Blend in flour, baking powder	and
salt.
Cover; chill
at least one hour.
Preheat oven to	400°.
Roll
dough 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut
into
desired shapes; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6
to 8 minutes or until very light brown.
Makes 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute rice and onion in oleo until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken with cheese and mushrooms
directions: Dredge flattened chicken breasts in flour, salt and pepper. Saute in the 1/2 stick of butter and oil until browned on both sides and cooked through.
Transfer chicken to a flameproof serving dish and keep warm.
Add to the pan the white and red wine and bring to a boil, stirring in the brown bits clinging to the bottom and sides of pan.
Simmer mixture for 3 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, cream and salt.
Mix well.
Add condensed milk and pour into freezer.
Add milk to the fill line and stir. Freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: hawaiian splendor sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add undrained pineapple and eggs.
Stir until combined.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Spread frosting over hot cake in pan.

title: easy salsa
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.
(Salsa gets hotter the longer it stands.)

title: don't pare pear pie
directions: Core and cut pears lengthwise.
Place cut side down in pie shell.
Beat ingredients and pour over pears.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Blend together until mixture resembles crumbs.
Add milk and stir until combined.
Roll dough; cut in 2-inch circles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden. Serve with creamed chicken.
Um, yum.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice peeled apples into baking dish.
Put water and cinnamon over apples. Sift together flour and sugar. Into sugar flour mixture, cut butter. Spread crumb mixture over apples and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a large pan.
Add the garlic and onion and saut until tender over low heat.
Add the bell pepper and saut three more minutes.
Crumble in the basil.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf and olives.
Bring to a boil, stirring several times.
Reduce heat to a simmer and add lemon slice.
Simmer for at least 20 minutes or as long as an hour.
Be sure to stir occasionally.

title: smoke sausage
directions: Cut sausage in 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook in water until water is almost out.
Add onions and bell pepper; continue cooking.
Add tomato paste and 1 cup water and simmer.
Delicious over rice.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion in butter; add ground beef and saute until well done.
Add kidney beans and juice, tomato soup, salt and chili powder.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain spinach, squeezing out as much of the water as possible. Mix all ingredients together and chill 1 hour.
Shape into balls. Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes approximately 40 balls.

title: mini cheese cake
directions: Blend until smooth the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Place 1 vanilla wafer in #2 aluminum lined cupcake holder, to be baked in cupcake tins.
Fill cupcake holder with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool and top with pie filling.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Let one frozen pie crust thaw for about ten minutes, then prick bottom of crust with a fork.
Bake according to package instructions; cool.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: turkey soup
directions: Put all the ingredients in a large pot.
Add 1 teaspoon Mrs. Dash (extra spicy) and 1/4 teaspoon chili powder.
Let all these ingredients simmer for 2 hours.

title: pecan pies
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bahama mama
directions: Add grenadine for color and freeze.

title: mike's favorite potato salad
directions: Mix dressing:
Miracle Whip, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine cake mix with remaining ingredients in a medium bowl and mix well.
Add more water if necessary.
Roll into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press lightly with a fork crisscross on each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sweet spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in a large pot covered with salted water.
Add dark beer, onion, garlic and mustard.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, onion, pimiento and lemon rind.
Add grated cheese, sherry, poultry seasoning and milk to mayonnaise.
Blend mayonnaise mixture thoroughly into chicken mixture.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until thoroughly hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off excess grease. Add salt, pepper and cream of mushroom soup. Mix well and let simmer. Prepare macaroni and cheese according to box. Add macaroni and cheese and hamburger mixture in a small dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving. Quick and delicious.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and mix with the crushed cereal; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish.
Top evenly with the cereal mixture. Bake for 55 minutes or until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend butter and Crisco together.
Sift sugar, flour and baking powder together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend dry mixture with the milk, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: steamed new potatoes and sesame carrots
directions: Scrub potatoes, but do not peel.
Slice thinly and place in steamer.
Peel and cut carrots into 3-inch sticks.
Place in steamer above potatoes.
Steam 15 minutes, until tender.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a medium skillet.
Add sesame seed and toast until golden.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter, honey and orange rind; blend well.
Remove carrots from steamer; toss in sesame glaze. Remove potatoes and sprinkle with parsley.

title: cashew chicken delish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add a small amount of water to create steam.
Cover baking dish with foil and bake 35 minutes.
Stir remaining ingredients together in a bowl and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients, in order, in blender.
Blend at "mix" speed until well blended.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: maple syrup dumplings
directions: Make up biscuit dough (stiff). Follow box directions. Pour syrup in large pan.
Very carefully bring to slow boil (medium heat as any higher syrup may scorch).
Carefully drop dough by the tablespoonful into syrup. Turn flame to very low and simmer until biscuits are done or no longer doughy inside. Eat warm or let cool.

title: clam fritter(serves 6)
directions: Drain clams and chop.
Sift all dry ingredients together. Combine eggs, milk, onion, butter and clams.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot fat (350°).
Fry about 3 minutes or until golden brown. Drain.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix marinade ingredients.
Add chicken and marinate overnight or up to 2 days; drain.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, turning wings every 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo and add to graham cracker crumbs; mix together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.

title: gram's corn fritters
directions: Mix all together except the egg whites.
After the ingredients are blended, fold in the beaten egg whites.
Drop by spoonful onto hot greased pan and fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook chicken until tender white over the stove, then add the vegetables.
When all is cooked, add soy sauce and cook for one more minute.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top	with
chocolate
bits.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, soups, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: round steak with tangy onion sauce
directions: Brown onions in 1 tablespoon butter in large frying pan; remove with slotted spoon and reserve.
Cut round steak into 6 serving size pieces; pound to 1/4-inch thick.
Brown beef (1/2 at a time).
Pour off drippings. Sprinkle salt and pepper over beef. Combine tomato sauce, vinegar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and cloves.
Pour over beef.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 1 hour.
Add onions and continue cooking, covered, 1/2 hour or until beef is tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate icing(very good with duncan hines butter recipe cake)
directions: Mix as listed.
Bring to a hard boil you cannot stir down. Cook one minute.
Stir continually while cooking.
Will cover eight thin layers.

title: mandarin pork or chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil; add garlic and pork or chicken and cook about 2 minutes.
Add broccoli, onions, carrots and celery.
Stir-fry 2 more minutes.
Add mushrooms and stir-fry an additional 2 minutes.
Add sauce and cook 1 more minute.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: bierocks
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until browned.
meanwhile, cut cabbage into large chunks and place into blender; put in enough water to cover and chop.
Or chop cabbage by hand.
Drain well. Add drained cabbage to hamburger.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook until cabbage is done.
Roll out 4 x 4-inch square of dough. Fill with mixture and seal by pinching sides shut.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: sherry walsh's corn meal chess pie(makes 2)
directions: Use spoon to mix.
Mix lemon and eggs; then add corn meal and sugar.
Add margarine and water.
Pour in unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups of the flour with the yeast.
Heat and stir milk, sugar, shortening and salt until warm.
Add to flour mixture. Add egg.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute and then at high for 3 minutes.
Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can mix in with a spoon.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Cream together the butter, brown sugar, egg, flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until light brown.
Cool.

title: french chocolate mousse
directions: Stir and scald milk, sugar and chocolate.
Pour part of these ingredients over egg yolks.
Return the sauce to the pan.
Stir custard constantly over low heat until it thickens.
Strain it. Cool by placing the pan in cold water.
In separate bowl, whip until stiff the cream.
Add vanilla and brandy.
Fold cold custard into cream mixture until well blended.
Fill custard cups with pudding.
Chill before serving.

title: superexcellent cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, baking in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, remove from oven and while cake is still hot, poke holes in it with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour condensed milk and caramel sauce together to mix; then pour into holes in cake.
Let cake cool for about 1 hour.
When cooled, spread entire cake with whipped topping.
Sprinkle crushed candy bars on top.
Refrigerate until served.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers) together in a greased baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle crackers on top and bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: terry's perfect muffins
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar (sugar may be omitted).
Combine beaten egg, milk and melted Crisco.
Turn liquids into dry ingredients; stir vigorously until all flour is dampened.
The batter will look lumpy (don't overstir).
Pour batter into greased or sprayed glass dishes.
(Muffin or cupcake pans can also be used, but they come out beautifully high in glass dishes.)
Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 30 minutes (less if you use tins).
Makes 5 large in glass dishes or 12 small in tins.

title: banana pepper relish
directions: Put peppers and onions through food processor.
Cover with boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt. Boil for 5 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: slaw
directions: Mix together Miracle Whip, milk, sugar and horseradish.
Pour over cabbage mix.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour before serving.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Bring shortening, sugar, molasses and vinegar to a boil. Cool.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well; chill.
Roll and cut out.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: *shrimp salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and French dressing.
Add all other ingredients.
Refrigerate for a short time.
Makes 4 servings. This salad is good served with tomato aspic ring or sliced tomatoes on lettuce.

title: barbecups
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onions and brown sugar; set aside.
Separate biscuits into 12 biscuits; place into 12 muffin cups in a muffin pan.
Spoon meat mixture into cups; sprinkle each with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: angel custard
directions: Cook in double boiler the first 4 ingredients until slightly thickened.
Add Knox gelatine which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup cold water.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add the vanilla, egg whites and sugar.
Fold into custard the whipped cream.
Break angel food cake into small pieces in shallow pan.
Pour custard over cake.
Chill 24 hours.
Serves 12.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a 10-inch Corning Ware or pie plate, layer ingredients in order.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes.
Serve with large Fritos or nacho chips.
This can also be heated in oven.

title: artichoke torte
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 3 tablespoons of the reserved artichoke hearts oil.
Mix artichoke hearts, grated cheese, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and eggs together.
Add onions and garlic.
Put into greased square 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with the crumbled soda crackers.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°. Chill for 2 hours before cutting.
Makes 10 servings.

title: liver sausage nut appetizer ball
directions: Mash liver sausage with fork to make smooth.
Add mayonnaise, dill pickle juice, Worcestershire, Tabasco, garlic salt and 1/3 of the cream cheese.
Blend by hand or mixer until smooth.
Stir in pickle and onion.
Pack firmly into a 2 cup mixing bowl lined with Saran or aluminum foil.
Chill several hours or until firm.
Turn out; frost with remaining softened cream cheese.
Chill well. Just before serving cover with peanuts.
Serve with crisp crackers.
Makes approximately 20 servings.

title: easy gingerbread men
directions: Combine cake mix, flour, eggs, oil, molasses and ginger (mixture will be soft).
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut with gingerbread man cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet 3 inches apart.
Decorate with assorted candies, decors or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges start to brown.
Remove immediately to cooling rack. Makes 12 to 14 (6-inch) men.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and put on cookie sheet in round teaspoonfuls; cookies don't spread.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: gigantic oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: *Pretoast oats in a single layer in a baking sheet, 10 to 12 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for several hours.

title: grape meat balls
directions: Mix together hamburger, onion, crackers, salt, pepper, egg and milk.
Roll into small balls.
Brown in hot oil.
Drain.
Put aside.
Mix together chili sauce, jelly and lemon in boiler. Bring to a boil.
Put meat balls in sauce and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugars in a large mixing bowl until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in pumpkin. Combine the flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, baking soda, salt and pecans in small bowl. Add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix just until blended.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean when inserted in center. Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: green beans and mushroom casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
In a casserole dish, mix everything together except 1/2 can of Durkee French onion rings.
Cook in oven for 15 minutes at 400°.
Put the remaining French onions on top.
Continue cooking for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine in saucepan, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Stir in cold water.
Simmer until smooth and thick, about 5 minutes.
Cool and add vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into a jar.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix flour, eggs and milk.
Heat in microwave until thickened (approximately 5 minutes).
Add vanilla and margarine.
In bowl, layer vanilla wafers, pineapple chunks and pudding.
Repeat, ending with wafers.
Make meringue with egg whites or use Cool Whip for topping.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add Tabasco (about a dash) and mustard.
Blend well.
Add shrimp and mix.
Leave in refrigerator at least 24 hours.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine graham crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine, mixing well.
Press into sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add 1 3/4 cups sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in sour cream and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn off oven and let cake remain in oven 45 minutes.
Open door but leave cheesecake an additional 45 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill overnight and cover with topping after removing spring-form pan.

title: zucchini crisp
directions: Simmer 15 minutes, then pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix 1/2 package of chopped beef (cut up well) with remaining ingredients and blend well.
Form into a ball and put remaining chopped beef on outside of cheese ball. Refrigerate to form.
Serve with crackers (Ritz).
Use 1/2 of ingredients for average size ball.

title: vegetarian split pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a soup kettle.
Simmer, covered, for 3 to 4 hours.
Or cook in slow cooker 8 to 10 hours on low, 3 to 4 hours on high.
Before serving, put the soup through a food processor or blender.
Add milk to cool when serving.
When serving, add cooked barley or grated cheese for a complete protein.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will keep up to two weeks.

title: cheesy pizza potatoes
directions: Mix
first
7 ingredients in skillet and brown together until onions
are
tender.
Put into casserole dish with 1 box Betty Crocker
au
gratin potatoes.
Add olives, water, milk, Italian pizza sauce and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender,
about
hour. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Put back into oven for about 5 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in 8-quart stockpot.
Fill pot to half full with water and add rest of ingredients.
(I omit the 1/2 cup rice and use 1/2 cup wild rice and also 1/2 cup barley.)
Add more water, as needed, to fill pot to 1-inch from top of pot. Simmer slowly for 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper as desired.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add sauerkraut last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: energy bars
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, peanut butter and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in 9 x 11 greased pan. Bake at 325-350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, nuts, apples, celery, and pineapple.
Toss with Miracle Whip and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: sauteed cherry tomatoes
directions: In a skillet over high heat, cook cherry tomatoes with sugar and salt in butter, stirring and shaking skillet often just until tomatoes are heated and skins start to wrinkle.

title: italian easy cassata cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions, pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and extract.
Pour over cake and mix in pan evenly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Frost cake with the following:
8 ounce container Cool Whip folded into lemon pie filling (pie filling mixed according to directions) or just plain lemon pie filling.

title: crabby deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks and set the whites aside. In a small bowl, mash yolks with a fork. Add crab, mayonnaise, relish, mustard, seafood seasoning and pepper, mixing well. Stuff or pipe into egg whites. Refrigerate until serving time. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet. Cool cookies on rack.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: You will also need olive oil spray.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda and sift again.
Cut fruit and flour with 1/2 flour.
Add spice to floured fruit.
Mix batter with 1/2 flour and grape juice.
Line pan with two layers waxed paper and grease. Bake 5 to 6 hours at 250°.
This recipe makes two 5 pound cakes. Use tube cake pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate thoroughly to blend the flavors. Great with vegetables, chips and pretzels.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix up the cream cheese with the cherries in a bowl with a fork or whip at a low speed in the blender.
Now, add the crushed pineapple after draining off the juice.
Prepare one envelope of Dream Whip and fold into mixture.
Add marshmallows and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream; cream together.
Spread over pizza dish.
Sprinkle with a little garlic salt.
Spread taco sauce.
Layer with lettuce, onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Mix ingredients together and let stand for 10 minutes.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on baking sheet.
Press out with spatula.
Brush with white of eggs and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Place 1/2 walnut in center.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandpa's stew
directions: Pressure meat with onion, salt, pepper and jalapeno pepper for 10 minutes after steam comes up.
Add corn, green beans, peas, celery, carrots and potatoes.
Pour meat juice over vegetables into roaster pan.
Add tomatoes and Snappy Tom.
Add catsup to taste.
Simmer until done or gone.

title: butterscotch-toffee fudge
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan.
Stir sugar, Marshmallow Creme and butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil, stirring constantly, 6 minutes. Remove from stove; stir in chips until melted, then toffee bars (toffee bars may not melt completely).
Pour into prepared pan and chill until firm.
With a sharp knife, cut into 1/4-inch squares. Store airtight in refrigerator.
Makes 36, about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: eye of round roast beef
directions: Sprinkle roast with all seasonings.
Sear all sides of roast in small amount of cooking oil in Dutch oven.
Add 4 cups of water and bouillon cubes.
Cover.
Cook about 2 to 3 hours in a 300° oven until roast is tender.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Saute peppers, celery and onions in butter until soft.
Blend in flour.
Add milk; cook until thickened.
Add cheese; blend well. Layer into casserole alternately with scallops.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All and corn that has been drained, onion and mayonnaise.
Place in a casserole dish; top with cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake until cheese is melted and cracker crumbs are browned.

title: creamy beef & macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add spaghetti sauce and Miracle Whip. (Miracle Whip Light may be substituted.) Stir with macaroni. Heat, topping with cheese. This freezes well. More cheese may be added on the plates.

title: fudge
directions: Mix and cook with lid on until it reaches 248° on candy thermometer.
When cooked, add enough cocoa to suit taste.
Also add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla to suit taste.
Beat until thick.

title: mom's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients in skillet.
Add 1/2 cup milk and mix well.
Add remaining milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Serve with butter over hot biscuits.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Spray nonstick frying pan with corn oil spray.
Add chicken and onion.
Cook until chicken is white and onion is translucent. Add peppers and celery while cooking and stirring.
Add pineapple and soy sauce.
Simmer, covered, for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: billy goat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter with sugar.
Separate 3 eggs.
Beat yolks and add to creamed mixture along with sour cream and vanilla.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Bring diet soda to a boil.
Add cornstarch and stir until thickened.
Add gelatin and continue stirring until boiling. Remove from heat and add sweetener.
Stir in sliced berries.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: cajun fried potatoes
directions: Cut the potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Add to boiling salted water; cook just until fork-tender but not mushy, about 7 minutes. Drain and cool.

title: ham soup
directions: Cook ham in water until soft.
Cut up and set aside.
Cook potatoes and onion in ham broth until tender.

title: t v mix
directions: Combine first four ingredients and pour over the remaining ingredients, which are combined in a large roaster pan.
Mix well. Bake in moderate to low oven for 1 hour, stirring occasionally with wooden spoon.

title: indonesia chicken
directions: Mix all above together and heat until bubbly; pour over chicken breasts or chicken on skewers which have been baked or grilled.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together and serve as vegetable dip.

title: pepper steaks
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika.
Brown meat and garlic in oleo in skillet.
Add water, soy sauce and bouillon.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add onions, cook 10 minutes.
Add green pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in blended cornstarch until thickened.
Serve over wild rice.

title: carrot salad 1
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over first mixture.
Mix together, cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold.
Goes well at a barbecue.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Stir the ingredients over low flame until cheese melts. Remove from heat and add 1 egg yolk.
Precook zucchini and put into baking dish; pour sauce over.
Sprinkle with some bread crumbs and some grated Parmesan cheese.
Put in oven or under broiler until top is brown.

title: honey dijon dressing
directions: Combine the yolks, mustard, honey, salt and lemon juice in a medium bowl.
Use a hand whisk, gradually add the oil, whisking continuously.
Stir in the half & half and blend well. Refrigerate.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: aunt mary's icebox cookies
directions: Mix together and put in bread tin overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° until done.
Do not overbake.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Press onto bottom and sides of ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Combine meat, cheese and green pepper.
Spoon over crust.
In small bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour top.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix butter, syrup and sugar.
Bring to a boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cream of tartar, salt and baking soda.
Stir until foamy and pour over popped corn. Spread on cookie sheet after mixing.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour. May add peanuts, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Mix corn and muffin mix.
Add well-beaten eggs, onion and green pepper.
Spoon into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and dot with sour cream.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: abondigas soup
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add bay leaves, tomato sauce, water, chicken bouillon and cumin.
Let boil.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake and cool 15 minutes. Poke lots of holes in cake with utility fork.
Meanwhile combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut in pan; bring to boil and simmer 1 minute.
Carefully spoon over warm cake.
Cool completely.
Fold 1/2 cup coconut into Cool Whip and spread over cake.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Keep remaining cake in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Gradually add flour, soda and salt. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350°
for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and put into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp sandwiches
directions: Mash shrimp; add garlic that has been mashed.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add other ingredients.
Make sandwiches.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into ball.
If too soft, chill for 5 or 10 minutes.
Using warm water on hands makes it easier to work with.
Spread chopped nuts on wax paper and roll ball in nuts until covered.
Wrap in foil or put in airtight container.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heavily butter deep casserole dish.
Layer half of chicken in the dish.
Sprinkle with garlic and chili powder.
Spread mushroom soup over chicken.
Sprinkle half of chopped onions over soup. Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over this.
Second layer is same except use chicken soup.
Top with Ro-Tel tomatoes that have been mashed well, then pour 1 cup of chicken broth over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes uncovered.
Cover and bake another 40 minutes. Remove from oven and allow to set on top of stove, at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: raphus' barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large pot (6 gallon pot).
Fill with water to make up the 6 gallons.
Bring to a boil.
Let set for 2 to 3 days in the refrigerator for full flavor.

title: beggs' favorite cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and butter; mix well. Reserve 1/2 cup mixture for topping.
Pat remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Beat with electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream; beat for 2 more minutes.
Pour into crumb-lined pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with reserved crumbs. Bake 10 minutes more.
Do not bake more than 30 minutes.
Turn off oven; leave ajar.
Leave cake in oven at least 1 hour. Refrigerate.

title: ice cream eggnog
directions: In a large bowl, beat the egg yolks; beat in 1/2 cup plus 1 tablespoon of the sugar and beat the mixture until it is light and lemon colored.
In another large bowl, beat the egg whites until they are frothy; beat in the remaining sugar and beat the whites until they hold soft peaks.
In a very large bowl, combine the egg whites and egg yolk mixture and stir in the milk, the rum and the bourbon.
Chill the eggnog, covered, overnight; transfer it to a punch bowl and stir in the ice cream, cut into small pieces.
Let the eggnog stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Soften cheese; beat until smooth.
Add sugar slowly.
Fold whipped cream into cheese mixture.
Fold pineapple into mixture. Pour into a 10-inch pan which has graham cracker crust. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream and chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup shredded cheese and tortillas.
Mix well.
Reserving some chicken mixture for top, fill each tortilla with generous serving spoon and roll up.
Place in lightly greased large casserole dish or divide into 2 square pans. (You may also spread a very thin layer of chicken mixture on bottom of casserole, if desired.)
Usually makes 8-10 enchiladas.
Cover enchiladas with remaining chicken mixture and shredded cheese. Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 30-45 minutes.
Garnish with additional green onions, black olives, salsa, etc.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in large bowl.
Mix dry pudding and Tang. Sprinkle over fruit and mix gently.
Let stand several hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: meatballs in mushroom soup
directions: In skillet, grease bottom of pan with 2 tablespoons mayo.
Mix hamburger, onion, salt and pepper in bowl and mix well.
Take 2 slices of bread and mix with a little water until moist, then pinch off pieces and put into mixture.
Stir all together and make into little balls.
Brown both sides until done in middle, then add 1 cup of water to mushroom soup in a bowl and stir.
Pour over meatballs and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in a 2-quart dish.
Microwave on High for 13 minutes, rotating about every 4 minutes.
Be sure mixture forms strings.
Stir in nuts.
Microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Add vanilla after 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in soda.
Pour into greased pan.

title: easy cherry punch
directions: Mix
punch
mix, cold water and Kool-Aid, stirring well. Add sugar;
stir until dissolved.
Add fruit juices; mix well. Serve from punch bowl with ice ring or ice cubes, if desired.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend together cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add and mix by hand the whipped cream, fruits and nuts.
Freeze in paper lined muffin pan.

title: piccallily
directions: Shred vegetables in food processor, and pour into a bowl. Add vinegar, sugar, salt, and spice.
Put into a boiling pot, and boil until transparent.
Piccallily is ready to be canned.
Yield 4-5 pt.

title: cashew rich cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except paprika.
Roll into ball.
Roll in paprika.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with different kinds of crackers or bread sticks.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Season cornmeal with salt and pepper.
Dredge tomatoes in cornmeal.
Fry immediately in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield 2 servings.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Bring chicken rice soup to a boil and dissolve in the jello. Stir well, set in refrigerator until partially set.
Whip cream and fold in jello.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Let sit overnight and serve.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften and mix cream cheese and margarine.
Stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; blend until smooth.
Stir in cake flour. Blend mixture until doughy texture.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: chicken and pastry
directions: Cook chicken until meat is tender.
Take meat out and pull off bones.
Drop pastry in chicken broth, one piece at a time.
Lower heat and cook until pastry is tender.
Place meat back in pot and enjoy.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes.
Put in casserole in layers with onion and cheese.
Add a little milk, not too much.
Bake in oven about an hour or until potatoes are soft at 350°.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Scald milk and pour into a large mixer bowl. Add shortening and sugar. Beat on low speed for a few seconds. Add 1 cup flour, yeast and beaten egg.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Cover bowl with damp cloth.

Put in warm place for 15 minutes. Add remaining flour. Stir with spoon. Turn dough on floured surface and knead lightly. Shape as desired. Cover and let rise about 20 minutes. Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all; stir well.
Cover; refrigerate 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken, celery, grapes, pineapple and
3 tablespoons of nuts together lightly.
Gently mix salad dressing and chicken mixture.
Chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.
Garnish with remaining nuts.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: laurie's garlic-herb cheese spread
directions: In a blender, blend well the cream cheese and sour cream or yogurt.
Mix in garlic, chives and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into small shallow dish and chill 3 hours. Serve with crackers, bread sticks or raw vegetables.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine
rice, soups, water and onion.
Place in bottom of baking
casserole.
Melt
butter.
Thoroughly
spread over chicken, using it all.
Salt and pepper chicken and lay on top of rice.
Bake
at
for
minutes or until chicken is tender and rice is done to taste.

title: barbecue sauce 2
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Marinate meat in sauce in refrigerator.
Great on pork.

title: zucchini pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Stir in pineapple and cinnamon.
Bake in large greased and floured cake pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
For a spicy cake add:

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain and rinse with cold water.
Cut up cheese and onion.
Break up corned beef and add noodles, cheese, onion, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Garnish with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; take cover off last 15 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese (soft) and onion soup mix.
Spread mixture on ham (thin).
Roll up.
With a sharp knife, cut in 3/4-inch pieces. Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening and peanut butter in with flour.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla. Add tablespoon of milk.
Mix all together until blended.
Make in to 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Mix well.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potatoes, and bake 1 hour at 350°. Reduce to 325° and bake for 2 hours. Add potatoes and bake another hour at 325°.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Combine and dissolve Jell-O, sugar and boiling water.
Stir in buttermilk, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Put into freezer tray and freeze.
Break into chunks.
Beat until smooth.
Add stiffly beaten egg white.
Return to freezer.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Beat butter in large bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour with baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in flavoring.

title: individual meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form balls and place in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish spice cookies(pepparkakor)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in egg. Mix in molasses. Sift flour with baking soda and spices.
Add to butter mixture gradually, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Chill overnight.

title: diet pie crust
directions: Squeeze cottage cheese dry in a piece of cheesecloth.
Press through a sieve.
Cut shortening into flour and salt until it looks like meal.
Add cottage cheese and mix well with a fork until it forms a ball of dough.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
For a cream pie, bake shell at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian volcano
directions: Put small mound of baking soda in pie plate.
Mix vinegar and food coloring.
Add liquid to baking soda.
Mixture will bubble and fizz just like volcano.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour two (9-inch) round layer pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) oblong pan.
Sift flour. Cream shortening until soft.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy after each addition.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add flour and bananas, alternately.
Blend well after each addition.
Bake 35 minutes for round layers.
Bake 45 minutes in oblong pan.

title: brownie cake
directions: Melt oleo, oil, cocoa and water together and bring to boil; then pour this over sugar and flour.
Mix and add eggs, soda, vanilla, buttermilk and cinnamon.
Mix well; batter will be thin. Grease cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn pie
directions: Fill crust with corn; dot with butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough milk to moisten.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: smoked brisket of beef
directions: Trim fat from brisket, and place in crock-pot.
Cover brisket with next 3 seasonings.
Add 1/2 bottle of liquid smoke.
Mix well. Cover overnight and all the next day on low.
Two to 3 hours before serving, remove brisket and slice thin (or shred each piece of meat with a fork).
Drain off most of liquid before returning brisket to crock-pot then cover with barbecue sauce.
Continue cooking 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with potato rolls as sandwich or as meat dish.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, sugar and cheese with other ingredients.
Mix together with cooked and drained spaghetti noodles.
Mix together remaining ingredients after placing in 2 large casserole dishes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover with foil while baking in a 9 x 13-inch dish is helpful.

title: spiced pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine sugar, salad oil and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each egg.
Gradually add the sifted ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and frost.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cinnamon and margarine.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla, salt and pecan halves.
Pour into a lightly buttered baking sheet.
Cool and separate.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Put all ingredients into food blender, except 3/4 cup salad oil.
Blend 15 seconds on medium speed.
Turn blender to high speed and dribble in remaining oil.
Keep refrigerated.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: coconut crust (9-inch)
directions: Spread butter on bottom and sides of an 8 or 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle coconut and press evenly into the butter.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Fill with cream filling.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix mayo, vinegar, milk and sugar. Add rest of ingredients. Keeps 2-3 weeks in fridge.

title: mother's apple pudding
