directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and let sit for 1 minute. Mix the next 3 ingredients with the above apple mixture. This will be a thick batter. Spread in a greased 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and eat while warm, especially good with the following sauce.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Melt 1/2 cup butter, add coconut and 1/2 cup pecans and cook over low heat until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese and condensed milk.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cheese mixture, caramel sauce and coconut mixture over crust.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Then transfer to refrigerator and keep in refrigerator until gone.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Add vegetables to beans.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine catsup, molasses and brown sugar.
Pour sauce over all. Place bacon strips on top.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears; reserve liquid.
Put pears in blender with whipping cream.
Blend.
Add cream cheese and banana; blend.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Boil and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour Jell-O into blender.
Blend all together. Pour into a bowl.
Refrigerate.
Allow to set.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Cover.

title: liver and onions
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Coat liver with flour mixture.
Brown in Crisco.
Then in deep baking dish, arrange liver and onions in layers.
Brown remaining flour until dark brown.
Add to liver and onion and pour in bouillon, dissolved in water for gravy.
Bake in oven 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Salt to taste.

title: easy doughnuts
directions: Take biscuits and cut holes in center.
Cook in grease in small saucepan.
When brown, remove and dip in frosting.

title: chop suey
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until clear.
Mix with remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Bake at 350°
for 55 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with chow mein noodles.
Return to oven and bake 10 more minutes.

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffee
directions: Make roux in a heavy skillet, cooking until mahogany-colored. Add onions, green pepper and celery to hot roux.
Cook, stirring often, until vegetables are slightly wilted and transparent, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste, cayenne and black pepper.
Stir in crawfish tails.
Slowly stir in stock or clam juice.
Season with salt.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.

title: apple pudding
directions: Fill a buttered baking dish half full of sliced apples.
Add sugar; pour over them a mixture of the butter, water, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Bake at 350° oven until browned. Serve with cream or milk.

title: lo-cal brownies
directions: Combine crumbs, cinnamon
and
salt.
Stir
in milk and vanilla, mixing well.
Add chocolate and nuts, blend thoroughly. Turn into a lightly greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes
or
just
until
done.
Turn
out on rack to cool.
Cut in	40
pieces, sprinkle powdered sugar over top if desired, approximately 44 calories per piece.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine
first	3
ingredients	in a small mixing bowl; beat well.
Add	milk,
corn
and
salt, stirring well.	Melt butter in a	1
1/2-quart
casserole
dish, then pour in corn mixture. Bake at
400° for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm and golden brown. Yield: 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together well. Add eggs, pumpkin, oil and vanilla. Bake in 4 one pound coffee cans or bread pans approximately 50 minutes at 375°.

title: crab delights fettuccini
directions: Cook fettuccini according to package directions.
Drain.
Heat butter and garlic in skillet on medium until garlic is lightly browned. Add half and half, Crab Delights and pepper.
Heat about 3 minutes or until mixture just begins to bubble, stirring occasionally.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Toss Crab Delights sauce with fettuccini.
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes four (1 cup) servings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 heaping tablespoonfuls per cup.
Fill up with boiling water.
Good with marshmallows.

title: all for one casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in iron skillet. Leaving in skillet, add soup and water; mix well. Prepare corn bread mix as package directs; spoon onto ground beef mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix egg, sugar, flour and margarine.
Do not beat, will be sort of pasty.
Put generous layer of peaches in a baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cut several slices of light bread in 2 inch strips.
Lay closely over peaches, then pour paste mixture over bread and peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bread is slightly brown.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk until thick.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip; blend well.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put down a graham cracker layer, then spread pudding mixture on graham cracker layer.
Layer graham crackers on top.
Frost with chocolate icing.
Chill 1/2 hour, then serve.
Serves 8 to 15.

title: apricot sticks
directions: Grind apricots and slowly bring all ingredients to a bubble, then cook for 10 minutes, stirring often. Cool enough to handle, then roll small stick size in granulated sugar. Put on waxed paper to cool and cut.

title: orange delite
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; save 3/4 cup for top.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Cream the sugar and eggs.
Add the pineapple, flour, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While cake is hot, prepare the icing and spread on cake.

title: butternut squash puff
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a sprayed 1-quart casserole.
Place in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is firm.
Great with chicken or turkey.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Blend together soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Layer carrots, peppers, onions and celery. Pour first mixture over layers of vegetables and let set overnight.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip for 2 minutes.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix strawberries and gel mix. Place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: glazed ham with peaches
directions: Cut ham slices 1/4-inch deep in a diamond pattern.
Place in ungreased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, mustard and allspice.
Add enough syrup to make a paste (about 1 tablespoon).
Spread over ham and bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: alma's apple fritters
directions: Peel the apples and cut them into 4 pieces each, place in a large pot in water.
Add the allspice and sugar, cook until apples are mushy.
Take biscuits and roll until they are completely flat, add 1 heaping spoonful into the middle of each biscuit, fold together and seal the edges together with a fork.
Put the apple fritters in oil until brown.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine apples with sugar and let stand at least 10 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend shortening and eggs; add to apples.
Now add dry ingredients.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin icebox dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Freeze. (Can be doubled and made in a 9 x 13 pan with graham cracker crust).

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Wash wild rice and boil about 20 minutes or until done. Drain.
Fry bacon.
Saute chopped onion, celery and green pepper. Mix all together in casserole, add water (1 to 2 cups).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream together your margarine and powdered sugar.
Then add your flour.
Make small balls and press with fork.
Bake about 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: pork chops
directions: Mix flour and bread crumbs.
Dip pork chops in mixture; brown in oil until golden brown.
Remove chops from pan.
Add cream of mushroom and onion soup with 2 cans of water; bring to a boil. Place pork chops in casserole dish; cover with gravy.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on thickness.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk in a glass 8 x 10-inch dish.
Put in microwave oven for 1 minute.
Stir and return for additional minute.
Remove and add nuts. Set in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian graham cracker cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, margarine, milk and vanilla.
Stir in crumbs with baking powder; mix well.
Fold in nuts, pineapple and coconut.

title: chicken pineapple salad
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch chunks.
Combine with celery and pineapple in a bowl.
Whisk cream and mayonnaise together until blended and pour over chicken.
Toss to coat thoroughly.
Season to taste.
Line 6 salad plates with lettuce leaves and mound on each plate.
Serve.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Keep at room temperature.

title: four bean salad
directions: Prepare lima beans and green beans as labels direct, but do not add salt to either.
In large bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix vinegar, sugar, oil, mustard, parsley and salt until well blended.
Add all kidney beans (rinsed and drained), lima beans and green beans, tossing gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours to blend flavors, occasionally stirring to mix. Makes 10 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: First Layer:
Mix together margarine, flour and nuts.
Press mixture to the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt or substitute on cabbage.
Let stand 1 hour. Squeeze water out and add carrots and sweet peppers.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar or sugar substitute, celery seed and mustard seed.
Boil one minute.
Cool and pour over cabbage.
Freeze in containers.
Thaw about an hour before using.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet.
Add celery, onion and pepper. Simmer until tender.
Add broth, rice and seasonings and stir. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all together, roll in sugar.
Cut into cookie shapes and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate mint surprise
directions: Cream all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and ice.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze in cupcake cups.

title: spanish sauce
directions: In a 8 quart double boiler saute oleo, onions and green peppers.
Add tomatoes.
Stir in sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Hold it hot in the double boiler.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together. Better to sit overnight. I usually double.

title: enchilada supreme
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, enchilada sauce and taco sauce.
Add browned, drained hamburger to mixture.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a baking pan.
Peel small to medium potatoes. Shake into plastic bag with cheese, salt and flour.
Place potatoes in the baking pan with melted butter.
Turn to coat with butter and bake in hot 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn potatoes with fork when they are golden brown.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil while kraut is draining.
Combine vegetables and add to drained kraut.
Pour vinegar mixture over kraut and vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: eggplant parmesan casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip slices of eggplant in egg.
Roll in flour and bread crumb mixture.
Cook in electric skillet with plenty of oil, 3 or 4 minutes per side.
Drain off excess oil. Place 1st layer in casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 sauce over eggplant layer.
Next add Parmesan cheese, dried onion, chili powder (to taste) and Mozzarella cheese.

title: mark's favorite fettucini
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, garlic, bell pepper and mushrooms in olive oil and wine.
Add seasonings to taste, i.e., basil, red pepper, garlic powder and salt.
Add shrimp.
Cook over medium-low heat until shrimp are done (10 minutes).
Mix cornstarch in cold half and half.
Pour into hot vegetables.
Turn up heat to thicken.
Add the rest of the half and half.
Turn heat to low and let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, while noodles cook. Stir often.
Serve over fettucini.
Serves 4.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels and margarine.
Mix and spread in 9 x 13 pan for bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and Dream Whip.
Spread over bottom layer tight to edges.
Refrigerate until set.
Dissolve jello in water, cool and add berries.
Pour over cream cheese layer and set.

title: red wine dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients blending thoroughly.
Lastly, mix in oil.
Chill.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; heat mixture to hard boil stage.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal; stir thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons onto buttered pan.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into cubes and combine with next 8 ingredients (celery, salt, tarragon, onion, juice, mayonnaise, vermouth and almonds).
Place in a buttered, shallow glass 2-quart casserole. Top with chips (or corn flakes) and grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In medium bowl, combine baking mix, milk and cheese; stir until just moistened.
Drop tablespoonfuls of dough, 2-3 inches apart, onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
In small bowl, combine margarine and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits.
Yields 6-8 biscuits.

title: parfait dessert
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour and melted margarine.
Add nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl, flour, sugar and cocoa.
Bring to boil butter, shortening and water; pour into bowl and beat well, then add milk, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, soda, and eggs; beat well. Pour onto greased sided sheet pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, melt 1/2 cup butter, 6 tablespoons milk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Bring just to boil and add 3 1/2 cups powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth and pour and spread over cake as soon as it is removed from oven.
Let cool.
Serve.

title: date cake
directions: Mix soda and hot water and pour over dates.
Let cool.
Mix sugar and butter; add egg, then flour, dates in water and vanilla. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Add cucumbers to water with lime mixed in.
Soak for 24 hours. Rinse.
Soak for 3 hours in clear water; drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and spices and add cucumbers.
Leave overnight. Drain out syrup and heat syrup to a boil, then add cucumbers and cook for 45 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
(Add a little green food coloring to make them look pretty.)

title: hot crab spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; blend in remaining ingredients except almonds and paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate. Top with almonds and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter until creamy.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, alternately with flour, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham-swiss cheese buns
directions: Cream butter, onion, mustard and poppy seed together.
Spread on cut side of buns.
Place slice of ham on bottom half of bun. Cover with slice of cheese.
Top with remaining half of bun.
Cook 3 sandwiches at a time for 2 minutes and 30 seconds in microwave oven.
Total cooking time:
about 5 minutes.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Separate broccoli flowerets and wash.
Cut stems into small pieces.
Chop eggs into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients in bowl large enough to stir well.
Better if made to let set overnight.

title: onion bread
directions: Cut loaf length wise.
Add onion mix to butter and spread on loaf.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: best ever baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until dark.
Add brown sugar and let melt over hamburger.
Add pork and beans and catsup to mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: soft spicy hermits
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda.
Add this mixture alternately with the milk and molasses to the creamed sugar and oil.
Stir in raisins.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in
a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: lattice gate cookies- hungarian
directions: Mix butter and flour as for pie crust.
Add sugar, soda and lemon rind.
Make small hollow in center; put in egg (I mix with fork first) and mix well.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Take 2/3 of dough and roll out to fit 11 x 15-inch pan.
Run dough part way up sides of pan.
Spread preserves on dough.
Roll rest of dough for top; cut in strips and lay in lattice design.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
In another bowl add 1 egg at a time to flour with a beater.
Add salt.
Mix flour mixture with sugar mixture and the remaining ingredients.
Flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (Bundt pan).

title: rum-raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine egg, sugar, butter, milk, rum, raisins and vanilla.
Stir until combined.

title: chili beans
directions: Wash beans and take out dirt or rocks.
Place in a large bean pot or large cooking pot with lid.
Cover beans with water.
Add salt pork, cut into small pieces.
Add chili peppers, onion, chili powder and tomato paste.
Cook slowly until done or soft, overnight in bean pot (slow).

title: church windows
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate and margarine, then cool.
Add colored miniature marshmallows and walnuts.
Shape into logs and roll in coconut.
Put in freezer until firm, then slice.

title: grape-nuts salad
directions: Beat egg white and sugar well.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: mexican fried ice cream
directions: Place 5 scoops of ice cream on a tray and freeze.
Mix cornflakes or tortilla crumbs with the sugar and cinnamon.
Dip frozen ice cream balls in crumb mixture, rolling to cover well. Freeze.
Remove frozen ice cream balls and dip in beaten egg. Roll again in crumbs.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, heat oil to 350°.
Dip balls in hot oil for 10 seconds.
Place in a bowl.
Top with caramel sauce.
Garnish with whipped cream and cherry.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1/4 cup warm water.
Heat buttermilk to lukewarm;
add
sugar,
salt,
shortening, soda, flour and dissolved yeast.
Knead
until
smooth.
Shape into rolls. Place in a warm
place.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until double.	Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato mix-up
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and fry until 1/2 done.
Cube onions, pepper and celery.
Add these and the rest of ingredients to bacon.
Cook on low, stirring often.
Doesn't hurt to mash up while cooking.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Good with eggs for breakfast or as a vegetable dish for any meal.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press in a greased 13 x 9-inch glass dish.

title: cottage and blue cheese dip
directions: Blend in blender until very smooth.

title: easy homemade pumpkin pie from your jack-o-lantern
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the milk and egg; add to first mixture.
Makes two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs, beat whites and add last.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add oleo and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beat well.
Add vanilla and buttermilk alternately with mixed dry ingredients.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in 4 layers or 3 (9-inch) pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Fry until crisp in heavy skillet; remove.
Cook onion and green pepper in bacon fat until golden. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 50 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove cloves and bay leaf.
Sprinkle crisp bacon over top.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients except sugar and set aside.
Mix oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts and apples.
Add dry ingredients and mix all together.
Mixture will be very thick.
Bake in 11 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 20.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain excess grease.
Mix tomato paste and 2 cans of water.
Pour into chuck.
Salt, pepper and add onion to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix and chill and serve.

title: beef broccoli pie
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions.
Drain fat.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic salt.
Add milk and softened cheese.
Cook and stir until smooth and bubbly. Stir 1 cup of hot mixture into beaten egg, return to mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in cooked broccoli; set aside.
Prepare pastry.
Spoon mixture in bottom crust.
Arrange cheese slices on top.
Cover with remaining crust.
Cut slashes on top and brush with milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; hold remaining ingredients.
Line 9 x 13-inch cake pan with frozen tortillas and pour meat mixture over it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cheese slices and return to oven until melted.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Slice or quarter.
Cover with an equal amount of sugar and vinegar.
Add a few pickling spices. Bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: breakfast colada
directions: Process the pineapple juice.
Run coconut cream, banana and ice cubes in a blender until smooth.
Pour into a tall glass and garnish with the lime slice.
Makes 1 drink.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Cook green peppers, celery and onion in oil and water for 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Mix soup mixture, noodles, tuna and 1/2 cheese and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: cheesy garden casserole
directions: Place cooked rice in the bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook broccoli, carrots, zucchini and green beans in boiling water about 5 to 7 minutes, or until just tender; drain well. Spoon vegetables over the rice.
Top with a mixture of tomato sauce, water, onion and oregano.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Combine the cheeses and sprinkle over the casserole.
Bake, uncovered, about 5 minutes longer, or until cheese melts.
Serves six.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt margarine and combine with all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into large baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is delicious served with ham.

title: tortilla shell snack
directions: Spread cream cheese over each tortilla.
Put peppers on top of cream cheese.
Roll up and chill in refrigerator until cool.
Cut in pieces and serve.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat.
Gradually stir in half and half, then add sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Bring to boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Store in a jar in the refrigerator.
Reheat to serve over ice cream.

title: tangy applesauce bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, butter, egg, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, applesauce and vanilla.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute, then increase speed to medium and beat for 2 minutes more.
Fold in 1 (8 ounce) package chopped dates and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 23 to 33 minutes.
Cool.

title: plain cake
directions: Put your
favorite icing on it.
It makes a good strawberry shortcake.

title: pork medallions with vegetables
directions: In medium saucepan, combine onion, celery, carrots, garlic, 1 cup water, bouillon cubes, tarragon and pepper.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes. DO NOT open oven door until cake has been baking at least 30 minutes.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in double boiler.
Mix in peanuts.
Add paraffin wax.
Spoon out onto waxed paper to cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until done. Skin, debone and cut into bite size pieces. Mix chicken broth, celery soup, chicken soup, peas, carrots and chicken well. Pour into 9x13 inch baking dish. Melt 1 stick oleo and mix well with the Bisquick gradually adding 2 cups milk. Pour over top of chicken mixture. Bake in pre-heated oven 375 degrees approximately 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.

title: chocolate sop
directions: Mix all together in saucepan and stir until thickened.
You may also mix in a microwave dish and cook 3 minutes on High in microwave.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Layer broccoli in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread cooked chicken on top.
In a large bowl, mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, sherry and curry powder together; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Bake uncovered.

title: sub sandwich
directions: Cut loaf of bread (longways) in half; cover bottom slice with lunch meats, then your cheese, lettuce, tomato slices and onion slices.

title: a poor man's frosting
directions: Mix and boil the flour and milk.
Cool in refrigerator, then add the remaining ingredients.
Beat on high speed until fluffy.

title: egg casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. Put into an 11 x 8-inch or 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter crunch pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and cook over low heat until it thickens.
Set aside.
Combine peanut butter with powdered sugar; mix together until forms small balls.
Bake pie shell; sprinkle with peanut butter mixture.
Add filling and top with remaining peanut butter mixture.
Makes one pie.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple and juice in 11 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Spread coconut evenly over pineapple.
Spread cake mix over coconut.
Cut butter into pats.
Place pats on top of cake mix. Place nuts on top of butter and press down lightly, not to bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Can substitute cherries
for
strawberries.
If you use apple pie filling, add 1 to 2 cans peaches.

title: rolled steak
directions: Wipe steak and sprinkle with flour.
Pound extra flour into steak.
Mix other ingredients and spread on steak, keeping mixture 1-inch from edge to prevent squeezing out.
Roll steak, tie securely and roast in a slow oven (300° to 350°) for about 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes lengthwise; scoop out potatoes (save the skins!).
Beat potatoes with all ingredients except crab meat and paprika. Fold in crab meat.
Refill potato shells and sprinkle with paprika.
Heat about 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven before serving.
Sprinkle with grated cheese or bacon pieces, if desired.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Make batter for cupcakes as directed on mix box.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter into ice cream cones; if you fill the cones too full, they will not have a round top.
Set on cookie sheet and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool and frost with any frosting mix.
Decorate with sprinkles and/or other things.

title: apricot tea
directions: Mix well.
Put in container with good lid.
To serve, put 4 teaspoons in a mug and cover with boiling water.
Enjoy!

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine in a large saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, about 15 to 20 minutes or until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. When cool, top with meringue made with the 3 leftover egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar. Brown meringue in hot oven.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yield: 16 servings, approximately 2 tablespoons per serving.
Contains 75 calories per serving.
Diabetic exchanges: 1/2 meat, 1 fat.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: In glass measuring cup, drain juice from pineapple.
Combine 1/4 cup juice with honey and lemon juice to taste in a large bowl. Add pineapple chunks, kiwi, berries and dates to bowl.
Mix lightly to coat.
Cover and chill for an hour.
Add bananas before serving.
Toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caraway meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup beer, egg, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in a roasting pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add hash browns.
Mix soup, sour cream and onion.
Pour over hash browns and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and return to oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: cocktail sausage
directions: Pour all 3 ingredients into a crock-pot and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted oleo and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° until apples are tender.
I usually add some sugar to apples.
Simple to make.

title: party potato salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard and salt. Chop eggs; if desired, save some slices for garnish.
Gently stir chopped eggs, potatoes, celery, sliced onions and pimento into dressing mixture.
Cover; refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Spread in greased pan.
Cut in squares.

title: chicken delight
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper and place in a greased baking dish.
Paint chicken with the salad dressing. Bake 25 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and continue baking until melted.
Glaze under broiler to brown, if desired.
Sprinkle parsley on top and serve.
Serves 4.

title: fish steaks with ginger honey mustard
directions: Combine mustard, mayonnaise, ginger, honey and thyme in a small bowl.
In a large shallow dish, coat fish with mustard mixture on both sides.
Cover with plastic wrap and marinate 30 minutes and refrigerate while preparing fire.

title: buttery yeast rolls
directions: Mix milk, butter, sugar and salt in a large bowl and let cool to lukewarm. Stir yeast into warm water and let stand 5 minutes to dissolve. Add 3 cups flour and dissolved yeast to first mixture and beat vigorously 2 minutes. Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk. Stir dough vigorously; add as much of remaining flour as necessary to knead dough. On a lightly floured board, knead for 1 to 2 minutes; let rest for 10 minutes. Resume kneading until smooth. Shape dough into a long, thin cylinder and with a floured knife cut off pieces of about 2/3-inch. Roll with hands on an unfloured board into a long, thin oval shape. Melt butter and let cool slightly. Dip each roll in melted butter and place close together in 2 loaf pans, or 3 if pans are small. Cover; let rise again until doubled. Preheat oven to 425° and bake for about 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. If bottoms of rolls are not sufficiently browned, remove from pan and place in oven, on rack, for a few minutes. Rolls will pull apart easily. Makes about 30 rolls.

title: jelly bar cookies(can cut in half.)
directions: Melt butter and stir into cake mix. Mix well; add egg yolks and stir until well blended. Press into 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and oil; beat well.
Mix	cocoa
and water together and add to mixture. Add flour,
baking
soda
and
baking
powder
and beat until smooth. Bake
at
For
2 (9-inch) pans bake 30 minutes and 9 x 13-inch pan, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crunchy caramel apple pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt. Add apple slices and gently toss until coated. Transfer apple mixture to pie shell and sprinkle Crumb Topping over the apple mixture. Place pie on cookie sheet and cover edges with aluminum foil. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 minutes. Remove foil and bake for another 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chopped pecans and drizzle caramel on top. Cool on wire rack and enjoy warm or at room temperature.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, egg, milk (enough milk to make it soupy) and salt and pepper.
Grease skillet and pour in skillet.
Bake at 350° until top is brown and crusty.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 8-inch ungreased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Needs no frosting.

title: poor man's pierogies
directions: Cook butter and onion in skillet. Pour 3/4 of the onions into the bottom of a Pyrex dish, reserving the remaining onion.
Cook bow ties.
Drain.
Put half of the bow ties on top of the onion in the Pyrex dish. Add cheeses and mashed potatoes.
Add the rest of the bow ties and mix.
Pour the rest of the butter and onions on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in round cake pan.
Use larger pan for thinner cornbread.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: betty rhule's soft icing
directions: Mix flour with water and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Soften butter and add Crisco.
Mix at high speed for 4 minutes.
Add sugar and mix again at high speed for 4 minutes.
Add flour mixture and beat an additional 4 minutes at high speed.
Stays soft.
May be frozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, salt, corn syrup, cooled melted butter and vanilla.
Spread nuts in pie shell and pour in filling.
Bake pie in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In 1-quart baking dish, coat with cooking spray.
Put corn and all other ingredients together and mix. Pour beaten egg in and mix well.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes, until mixture is thick or bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: apple rings
directions: Cut apples in rings after peeling and coring.
Bring to a good boil the water, sugar, vinegar and spices. Drop apples in and cook slowly until tender. Color with red food coloring, if desired.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop dough by round tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: sherry buttered chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts until 1/4 inch thick.
Mix egg and water, then mix crumbs and cheese.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then crumb mixture.
Place single layer in ovenproof dish.
In small saucepan cook margarine, sherry, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and Dijon mustard to boil; pour over chicken. Broil in 500° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Put mayonnaise, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper in jar and shake.
Pour in with cabbage, carrot and other ingredients and stir.

title: snack sandwich
directions: Brown meat, then drain.
Melt cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Place on rye bread and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; mix well.
Add butter, eggs, milk and vanilla; stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into crust. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: aloha fresh fruit punch
directions: Combine pineapple chunks, brown sugar, vanilla bean and nutmeg; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
At serving time, remove and discard vanilla bean.
Put pineapple mixture in a punch bowl.
Add orange sections, grapefruit sections, lime juice, pineapple juice and grape juice. Stir gently.
Yield:
18 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo and eggs.
Pour milk over oatmeal, then add salt and baking powder.
Add oatmeal mixture to sugar mixture. Bake in buttered pan at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Top with milk and cinnamon for a delightful breakfast dish.

title: spinach frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Parboil and drain spinach thoroughly. Blend with cottage cheese, 3/4 cup bread crumbs and Romano.
In separate bowl, beat 3 eggs well and blend into spinach mixture.

title: dilled red potato salad
directions: Combine mustard, vinegar, dill, mayonnaise and seasoned salt in a small bowl.
Toss over potatoes and onions.
Correct seasoning as necessary.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in glass pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix the two ingredients together.
May be used on other fresh fruit.

title: bisquick bars
directions: Combine Bisquick and brown sugar.
Add eggs, nuts, vanilla and oatmeal, if used.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 30 to 40 squares.

title: creamy pesto pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Drain well.
Keep warm. Meanwhile, in a medium skillet, cook basil and garlic in hot oil about 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Add cream, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Heat and stir until fairly smooth.
Stir in wine, parsley and water.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Serve sauce over hot cooked pasta.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and set aside.
Mix all ingredients together, then add cooked broccoli.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with bread crumbs.
Cook in 2-quart casserole in microwave uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes on Full power, or bake 45 minutes in regular 350° oven or until knife comes out clean when inserted in the middle.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter thoroughly.
If using mini chips, mixture can be rolled into 1-inch balls and rolled into chips.
Otherwise, melt chocolate with a small piece of paraffin and dip balls into melted chocolate to coat.

title: blackbottoms
directions: Combine cream cheese, beaten egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Set aside. Sift together 1 1/2 cups flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla to flour mixture.
Beat well.
Fill small cupcake liners placed in muffin tin half full of flour mixture.
Drop approximately 3/4 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture on top of each cupcake.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 45 miniature cupcakes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy, using electric mixer at medium speed. Beat in egg.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: * May use 1 teaspoon of each of the following: vanilla, lemon and almond flavorings.

title: real italian sauce
directions: Brown meat in olive oil and garlic.
Add all other ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over mostaccioli noodles.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in large saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat; stirring gently.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks lightly in small bowl; gradually whisk in 1 cup of hot mixture and return to saucepan.
Return to boil and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Coarsely chop chocolate.
Whisk in chocolate, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cook 15 minutes on wire rack.
Cover with wax paper.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Top with sweetened whipped cream.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients except lemon slices and uncooked shrimp.
Pour about 1/2 cup of sauce to cover the bottom of a large baking dish and arrange layers of shrimp and lemon slices, leaving 1 or 1 1/2 inches to top of dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shrimp.
Bake, uncovered, stirring once or twice, until shrimp are cooked through, 15 to 20 minutes.
Your guests should peel their own shrimp and dip French bread in sauce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry-apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium-sized saucepan, combine cranberry-raspberry sauce, apples, brown sugar and cornstarch, stirring to mix well.
Over medium-high heat, cook 5 minutes until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
